The Journal of Julius Rodman , Being an Account of the First Passage across the Rocky Mountains of North America Ever Achieved by Civilized Man is an unfinished serial novel by American author Edgar Allan Poe published in 1840 .
East of the Mountains is a novel by American author David Guterson , first published in 1999 , and in paperback in 2000 .
The Marvels Project is a 2009 - 2010 eight - issue comic book limited series written by Ed Brubaker with art by Steve Epting and published by Marvel Comics .
La sombra de Heidegger ( English : The Shadow of Heidegger ) is a 2005 thriller written by the Argentine philosopher José Pablo Feinmann .
Works of Love ( Danish : Kjerlighedens Gjerninger ) is a work by Søren Kierkegaard written in 1847 .
Firewing is a children 's book written by the Canadian author , Kenneth Oppel .
The Age of Spiritual Machines is a non - fiction book by inventor and futurist Ray Kurzweil about artificial intelligence and the future course of humanity .
O Seminarista ( in English : The Seminarian ) is a novel by Brazilian writer Bernardo Guimarães , first published in 1872 .
To Kill a Mockingbird is a novel by Harper Lee published in 1960 .
Gut Symmetries is a 1997 novel by the British literary writer Jeanette Winterson , exploring themes of human relationships and physics .
The Underpainter is a novel by Jane Urquhart that won the 1997 Governor General 's Award for English - language fiction , and in the same year was a finalist for the Rogers Writers ' Trust Fiction Prize .
The Four - Chambered Heart is a 1950 autobiographical novel by French - born writer Anaïs Nin , part of her Cities of the Interior sequence .
`` The Secret Sharer '' is a short story by Joseph Conrad written in 1909 , first published in Harper 's Magazine in 1910 , and as a book in the short - story collection Twixt Land and Sea ( 1912 ) .
Little Peter 's Journey to the Moon ( German Peterchens Mondfahrt ) is a German - language fairy tale written by Gerdt von Bassewitz .
Sonnet 36 is one of 154 Shakespeare 's sonnets written by the English playwright and poet William Shakespeare .
Lettin ' It All Hang Out is the autobiography of drag performer RuPaul .
Nightmares and Geezenstacks is a short story collection consisting of 47 horror , science fiction and crime stories written by Fredric Brown .
Les Contemplations ( The Contemplations ) is a collection of poetry by Victor Hugo , published in 1856 .
Spearfield 's Daughter is a 1982 novel written by Australian author Jon Cleary .
`` The Sick Rose '' is a poem by William Blake .
Sigtuna väravad ( English : The Gates of Sigtuna ) is a compilation of novels by Estonian author Karl Ristikivi .
The Rottweiler ( 2003 ) is a psychological thriller novel by English crime writer Ruth Rendell .
Les Sœurs Vatard ( English : The Vatard Sisters ) is a novel by the French writer Joris - Karl Huysmans , first published in 1879 .
The Emerald Atlas is the first novel of the children 's fantasy trilogy The Books of Beginning by John Stephens .
The Meanest Doll in the World is a children 's novel by Ann M. Martin and Laura Godwin .
`` Black Colossus '' is one of the original short stories starring the fictional sword and sorcery hero Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard and first published in Weird Tales magazine , June 1933 .
Up the Junction is a 1963 collection of short stories by Nell Dunn that depicts contemporary life in the industrial slums of Battersea and Clapham Junction .
Witch Week is a children 's fantasy novel and school story by the British writer Diana Wynne Jones , published by Macmillan Children 's Books in 1982 .
La Dentellière ( `` The Lacemaker '' ) , is a French novel by Pascal Lainé .
An Encyclopedia of Claims , Frauds , and Hoaxes of the Occult and Supernatural is a 1995 book by James Randi with a foreword by Arthur C. Clarke .
Beyond the Veil of Stars is a science - fiction novel by Robert Reed , first published in 1994 .
Goblin Market and Other Poems was Christina Rossetti 's first volume of poetry , published in 1862 .
The Key to Midnight is a novel by the best - selling author Dean Koontz , released in 1979 under the pseudonym Leigh Nichols .
The Headless Lady ( 1940 ) is a whodunnit mystery novel written by Clayton Rawson .
The Rites of Eleusis were a series of seven public invocations or rites written by British occultist Aleister Crowley , each centered on one of the seven classical planets of antiquity .
One Man 's Bible ( S : 一个人的圣经 , T : 一個人的聖經 , P : Yī gè rén de Shèngjīng , French : Le Livre d'un homme seul ) is a novel by Gao Xingjian .
A View from the Bridge is a play by American playwright Arthur Miller , first staged on September 29 , 1955 , as a one - act verse drama with A Memory of Two Mondays at the Coronet Theatre on Broadway .
Hinds ' Feet on High Places is an allegorical novel by English author Hannah Hurnard .
Black Kiss is a hardboiled erotic American comic book limited series written and drawn by Howard Chaykin , which was originally published in 1988 by Vortex Comics .
Hell Has No Limits ( Spanish : El lugar sin límites , `` The Place Without Limits '' ) is a 1966 novel written by Chilean José Donoso .
Guerrilla Days in Ireland is a book published by Irish Republican Army leader Tom Barry in 1949 .
Emeka a biography by Frederick Forsyth about his friend Colonel Chukwuemeka Odumegwu Ojukwu , head of the state of Biafra , a republic that seceded from Nigeria and was briefly independent .
Killing Rommel is a 2008 historical fiction novel by Steven Pressfield set in North Africa during World War Two .
The Heart of Midlothian is the seventh of Sir Walter Scott 's Waverley Novels .
Absent in the Spring is a novel written by Agatha Christie and first published in the UK by Collins in August 1944 and in the US by Farrar & Rinehart later in the same year .
An Essay on the History of Civil Society is a book by the Scottish Enlightenment philosopher Adam Ferguson , first published in 1767 .
Chuk and Gek ( Russian : Чук и Гек ) is a 1939 Russian short - story written by Soviet children 's writer Arkady Gaidar .
`` Gingo biloba '' ( later : Ginkgo biloba ) is a poem written by the German poet Johann Wolfgang von Goethe .
His Family is a novel by Ernest Poole published in 1917 about the life of a New York widower and his three daughters in the 1910s .
The Three Sui Quash the Demons ' Revolt ( 三遂平妖傳 ) , also translated as The Sorcerer 's Revolt , is a novel written in the Ming Dynasty and attributed to Luo Guanzhong , the 14th - century author of Romance of the Three Kingdoms .
Soldier Boys is a 2001 novel by writer Dean Hughes .
The Boat of a Million Years is a science fiction novel by Poul Anderson first published in 1989 and nominated for the Nebula Award for Best Novel that same year .
The Conan Grimoire is a 1972 collection of essays , poetry and fiction edited by L. Sprague de Camp and George H. Scithers , published in hardcover by Mirage Press .
The Meaning of Shakespeare ( 1951 ) was written by Harold Clarke Goddard .
Det skriker fra Kverrvilljuvet is a novel first published in 1920 by Norwegian writer Mikkjel Fønhus .

The Extraordinary Life of The Last Emperor of China ( Chinese : 末代皇帝的非常人生 ; pinyin : Mòdài Huángdì dè Fēicháng Rénshēng ) is a Chinese historical biographical book by Jia Yinghua about the life of Puyi ( 1906 - -1967 ) , the Last Emperor of China .
Phineas Finn is a novel by Anthony Trollope and the name of its leading character .
The Myth of the Twentieth Century ( German : Der Mythus des zwanzigsten Jahrhunderts ) is a 1930 book by Alfred Rosenberg , one of the principal ideologues of the Nazi Party and editor of the Nazi paper Völkischer Beobachter .
Swordsmen and Supermen is an anonymously edited anthology of fantasy stories by Robert E. Howard and others , with a cover by Virgil Finlay .
Hello Out There ! is a one - act play by the Armenian - American playwright William Saroyan written early in August 1941 .
`` The Brick Moon '' is a short story by Edward Everett Hale , published serially in The Atlantic Monthly starting in 1869 .
Journey to a War is a travel book in prose and verse by W. H. Auden and Christopher Isherwood , published in 1939 .
`` A Retrieved Reformation '' is a short story by American author O. Henry first published in The Cosmopolitan Magazine , April 1903 .
Kiss Me , Deadly ( 1952 ) is Mickey Spillane 's sixth novel featuring private investigator Mike Hammer .
Postcards from the Grave is a book by Emir Suljagić , relating to his experiences in Srebrenica , published on 31 July 2005 by Saqi Books ( 196 pages ) .
Traditionally , the authorship of the Mahabharata is attributed to Vyasa .
The Story of My Typewriter is a 2002 book , by Paul Auster , mostly with pictures by the painter Sam Messer .
Fashion Beast is a 2012 ten issue limited series and screen play by Alan Moore , Malcolm McLaren , and Antony Johnston .
China Harayeko Manchhe is an autobiography written by Hari Bansha Acharya .
The Star Rover is a novel by American writer Jack London published in 1915 ( published in the United Kingdom as The Jacket ) .
`` The Ones Who Walk Away from Omelas '' is a 1973 plotless , short , descriptive work of philosophical fiction , popularly classified as a short story , by Ursula K. Le Guin .
The Four Elements of Architecture is a book by the German architect Gottfried Semper .
The Jupiter Theft is a 1977 novel by science fiction writer Donald Moffitt , re - printed in 2003 with a new afterword .
`` Harrison Bergeron '' is a satirical and dystopian science - fiction short story written by Kurt Vonnegut and first published in October 1961 .
The Blue Peril ( English translation of the French title , Le Péril Bleu ) is a 1910 French science fiction novel by Maurice Renard .
Emilia Galotti is a play in five acts by Gotthold Ephraim Lessing ( 1729 - -1781 ) , which premiered on 8 March 1772 in Brunswick ( `` Braunschweig '' in German ) .
The Chinaman Pacific and Frisco R.R. Co. is a 1988 short - story collection by Frank Chin that collects many of the short stories he had published in the 1970s .
Notes on Muscovite Affairs ( Rerum Moscoviticarum Commentarii ) ( 1549 ) was a Latin book by Baron Sigismund von Herberstein on the geography , history and customs of Muscovy ( the 16th century Russian state ) .
Obasan is a novel by the Japanese - Canadian author Joy Kogawa .
Room For Love is a chick lit novel by American author Andrea Meyer .
Heart of the Comet is a novel by David Brin and Gregory Benford about human space travel to Halley 's Comet published in 1986 .
`` The Revolutionist '' is an Ernest Hemingway short story published in his first American volume of stories In Our Time .
Lords of the Starship is a 1967 science fiction novel which marked the debut of author Mark S. Geston , written while he was a sophomore at Kenyon College .
Märchen Awakens Romance , officially abbreviated as MÄR ( メル Meru ) , is a manga series written and illustrated by Nobuyuki Anzai .
Seen Art ? is a children 's picture book written by Jon Scieszka and illustrated by Lane Smith .
De humani corporis fabrica libri septem ( Latin for `` On the fabric of the human body in seven books '' ) is a set of books on human anatomy written by Andreas Vesalius ( 1514 - -1564 ) and published in 1543 .

Oath of Swords is the first novel in the War God fantasy series by American author David Weber .
Brian 's Return is a 1999 wilderness survival novel written by Gary Paulsen and fourth novel in the Hatchet series .
El Unicorno translated in English as The Wandering Unicorn ( 1965 ) is a novel by the Argentinian author Manuel Mujica Láinez ( 1910 - -1964 ) in which the legend of Melusine is developed .
The Symbolic Species is a 1997 book by biological anthropologist Terrence Deacon on the evolution of language .
Where to Find Your Law is a book by Ernest Arthur Jelf , M.A. It is a bibliography of law .
Lucky Everyday ( 2009 ) is the debut novel of the Indian author Bapsy Jain published by Penguin , USA .
Elements of the Philosophy of Newton ( French : Éléments de la philosophie de Newton ) is a book written by the philosopher Voltaire in 1738 that helped to popularize the theories and thought of Isaac Newton .
Drømmebroer ( lit . Dream Bridges ) is a 2000 poetry collection by Danish poet Henrik Nordbrandt .
The Theory of Business Enterprise is an economics ( or political economy ) book by Thorstein Veblen published in 1904 that looks at the growing corporate domination of culture and the economy .
The Eyes of the Dragon is a novel by Stephen King that was first published as a limited edition slipcased hardcover by Philtrum Press in 1984 , illustrated by Kenneth R. Linkhauser .
The Monkey Wrench Gang is a novel written by American author Edward Abbey ( 1927 - -1989 ) , published in 1975 .
The Stain is a 1984 novel of sexuality and religion by Rikki Ducornet , set in France 's Loire Valley in the nineteenth century .
The Clerkenwell Tales is an historical novel by English writer Peter Ackroyd , first published in 2003 .
How I Became a Nun by César Aira is a novel set in Rosario , Argentina , about a precocious six - year - old named César Aira .
The Wheel on the School is a novel by Meindert DeJong a Dutch born American that won the 1955 Newbery Medal for children 's literature and the 1957 Deutscher Jugendliteraturpreis .
Al Capone Does My Shirts is a historical fiction novel for young adults by award winning author Gennifer Choldenko .

It 's Just a Plant is a children 's book , written , illustrated and published by Ricardo Cortés .

The Totem is a horror novel by David Morrell , first published in 1979 .

The Ring and the Book is a long dramatic narrative poem , and , more specifically , a verse novel , of 21,000 lines , written by Robert Browning .

`` Down by the Salley Gardens '' ( Irish : Gort na Saileán ) is a poem by William Butler Yeats published in The Wanderings of Oisin and Other Poems in 1889 .

32 Aquarii ( abbreviated 32 Aqr ) is a spectroscopic binary star in the constellation of Aquarius .

Hercules Dome ( 86 ° S 105 ° W ) is a large ice dome between the Thiel Mountains and the Horlick Mountains in Antarctica .
Mount Tchaikovsky ( 71 ° 23′S 73 ° 15′W ) is a snow - covered mountain , rising to about 600 m , with scarps on the south and east sides , located in the north part of Derocher Peninsula , situated in the southwest portion of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Lawrence Nunatak ( 84 ° 50′S 67 ° 2′W ) is a nunatak , 1,540 metres ( 5,050 ft ) high , standing 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Snake Ridge along the ice escarpment that trends southwest from the ridge , in the Patuxent Range of the Pensacola Mountains , Antarctica .
Freshfield Nunatak ( 80 ° 28′S 24 ° 53′W ) is an isolated nunatak rising to about 1,450 metres ( 4,760 ft ) to the southeast of the Herbert Mountains in the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Cape Lindsey is a cape which forms the western extremity of Elephant Island in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Stubel Hill ( Bulgarian : Стубелски хълм , `` Stubelski Halm '' \'stu - bel - ski ' h&lm\ ) is the ice - covered hill rising to 485 m and forming the north extremity of Marescot Ridge on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Gaul Cove ( 67 ° 49′S 67 ° 11′W ) is a cove indenting the northeast side of Horseshoe Island , off the coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Edward Ridge ( 67 ° 15′S 55 ° 34′E ) is a gently rising , snow - covered ridge standing 13 nautical miles ( 24 km ) northwest of Rayner Peak in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Polar Subglacial Basin ( 85 ° 0′S 110 ° 0′E ) is a subglacial basin situated generally between Gamburtsev Subglacial Mountains and the Dominion Range in East Antarctica .
The Kjølrabbane Hills ( 72 ° 16′S 3 ° 22′W ) are a small group of hills between Lyftingen Peak and the Styrbordsknattane Peaks , near the southwest end of Ahlmann Ridge in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Gerry Glacier ( 77 ° 24′S 152 ° 5′W ) is a glacier on Edward VII Peninsula , Antarctica , flowing north between Reeves Peninsula and the Howard Heights to the head of Sulzberger Bay .
Dick Glacier ( 84 ° 53′S 175 ° 50′W ) is a tributary glacier , 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) long , flowing west from Mount Campbell to enter Shackleton Glacier just north of Taylor Nunatak , in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Winter Quarters Bay is a small cove of McMurdo Sound , Antarctica , located 2,200 miles ( 3,500 km ) due south of New Zealand at 77 ° 50'S.
Frustration Ridge is a ridge forming the northern end of the Cobham Range in the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
Bangladesh ( /bɑːŋlɑːdɛʃ/ ; i/ˌbæŋɡləˈdæʃ/ ; বাংলাদেশ , pronounced : ( ˈbaŋlad̪eʃ ) , lit . `` The land of Bengal '' ) , officially the People 's Republic of Bangladesh ( গণপ্রজাতন্ত্রী বাংলাদেশ Gônôprôjatôntri Bangladesh ) , is a country in South Asia .
Siniger Nunatak ( Bulgarian : нунатак Синигер , `` Nunatak Siniger '' \'nu - na - tak si-'ni - ger\ ) is the rocky hill rising to over 500 m in the upper course of Russell East Glacier on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Canine Hills ( 71 ° 37′S 163 ° 50′E ) are a line of mostly snow - covered hills and ridges trending northwest -- southeast for 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) and forming the eastern half of Molar Massif in the Bowers Mountains , a major mountain range situated in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Albanus Glacier ( 85 ° 52′S 151 ° 0′W ) , also known as Phillips Glacier , is a 25-mile ( 40 km ) long glacier flowing west along the south side of Tapley Mountains to enter Scott Glacier just north of Mount Zanuck , in the Queen Maud Mountains in Antarctica .
Fishtail Point ( 78 ° 57′S 162 ° 36′E ) is the southernmost point of Shults Peninsula , at the east side of the mouth of Skelton Glacier in Antarctica .
Aster Glacier ( 78 ° 35′S 85 ° 0′W ) is an Antarctic glacier descending the east slope of Craddock Massif and flowing between Elfring Peak and Willis Ridge into Thomas Glacier in the Sentinel Range , Ellsworth Mountains in Antarctica .
Mount Faith ( 69 ° 37′S 64 ° 29′W ) is a massive mountain 9 nautical miles ( 17 km ) north of Mount Hope , rising to 2,650 metres ( 8,700 ft ) from the northern end of the Eternity Range in northern Palmer Land , Antarctica .
The Grunehogna Peaks ( 72 ° 3′S 2 ° 47′W ) are a group of peaks 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) north of the Liljequist Heights , in the south part of Ahlmann Ridge in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Chavdar Peninsula ( Poluostrov Chavdar \po - lu-'os - trov chav-'dar\ ) is a 10-km wide peninsula projecting 13 km in northwest direction from Graham Land on the Antarctic Peninsula in Antarctica .
The Lachal Bluffs ( 67 ° 30′S 61 ° 9′E ) are a group of rocky headlands located just south of Ufs Island and east of Howard Bay , and about 4 kilometres ( 2.5 mi ) west of Allison Bay , on the Mawson Coast of Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica .
Steventon Island ( 77 ° 15′S 148 ° 15′W ) is a broad ice - covered island about 39 km ( 24 mi ) long off of Antarctica , lying west of Court Ridge in the Sulzberger Ice Shelf .
Mount Freya is a prominent peak east of Mount Thor in the Asgard Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Kaminuma Bluff ( 77 ° 36′S 168 ° 57′E ) is a bold ice - covered bluff that rises to over 200 metres ( 660 ft ) near the shore in southeastern Ross Island , off the coast of Antarctica .
Mount Langway ( 75 ° 29′S 139 ° 47′W ) is a coastal mountain , 760 metres ( 2,500 ft ) high , located 2.5 nautical miles ( 5 km ) southwest of Mount LeMasurier in the Ickes Mountains of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Kreitzer Glacier ( 70 ° 22′S 72 ° 36′E ) is a glacier flowing northwest between Jennings Promontory and the Reinbolt Hills into the eastern part of the Amery Ice Shelf , Antarctica .
Berry Bastion ( 80 ° 13′S 157 ° 11′E ) is a large , mostly ice - covered mountain in Antarctica with abrupt north facing rock cliffs .
Jackson Tooth ( 80 ° 25′S 23 ° 16′W ) is a nunatak rising to 1,215 metres ( 3,990 ft ) at the western end of Pioneers Escarpment , in the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Ivanoff Head ( 66 ° 53′S 109 ° 7′E ) is a small rocky headland , or probable island , which lies along the coast and is partly overlain by continental ice , situated 4 miles ( 6.4 km ) west of the Hatch Islands at the head of Vincennes Bay , Antarctica .
Landmark Peak ( 79 ° 10′S 85 ° 40′W ) is a very prominent peak , 1,840 metres ( 6,040 ft ) high , standing 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) south of Minnesota Glacier on the east side of Gowan Glacier , in the Heritage Range , Antarctica .
The 2012 Asia - Pacific Economic Cooperation summit was held on Russky Island and about $ US6 billion was set aside for the development of the island and Vladivostok in preparation for the summit .
Table Mountain ( Khoikhoi : Hoerikwaggo , Afrikaans : Tafelberg ) is a flat - topped mountain forming a prominent landmark overlooking the city of Cape Town in South Africa , and is featured in the Flag of Cape Town and other local government insignia .
The Apocalypse Peaks ( 77 ° 23′S 160 ° 51′E ) are a group of peaks with a highest point of 2,360 metres ( 7,740 ft ) , standing east of Willett Range and between Barwick Valley and Balham Valley , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Moore Mountains ( 83 ° 21′S 160 ° 45′E ) are a small but conspicuous group of mountains just north of New Year Pass in the Queen Elizabeth Range in Antarctica .
Kizer Island is an ice - covered island about 30 kilometres ( 15 nmi ) long , lying 20 kilometres ( 10 nmi ) southwest of Cronenwett Island at the west end of the Sulzberger Ice Shelf , Antarctica .
Mount McCauley ( 73 ° 12′S 63 ° 15′E ) is a prominent mountain between Mount Scherger and Mount Dummett on the north side of Fisher Glacier , in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Somovit Point ( Bulgarian : нос Сомовит , `` Nos Somovit '' \'nos ' so - mo - vit\ ) is a point on the east coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica projecting 500 m into Bransfield Strait between Kruni Cove and Tsepina Cove .
Mount Guéguen ( 65 ° 4′S 64 ° 0′W ) is a sharp rocky peak , 365 metres ( 1,200 ft ) high , standing 0.25 nautical miles ( 0.5 km ) northwest of Louise Peak in the northern part of Booth Island , in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Tuorda Peak ( 65 ° 59′S 65 ° 10′W ) is a peak , 870 m , rising eastward of Ferin Head on Velingrad Peninsula , the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Manahan Peak ( 77 ° 29′S 168 ° 26′E ) is a prominent peak 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) east of Giggenbach Ridge in northeastern Ross Island , Antarctica .
Hannah Point is a point on the south coast of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Wednesday Island is an island 1 nautical mile ( 1.9 km ; 1.2 mi ) long , at the east end of Wauwermans Islands in the north part of Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .

Ferdinand Paul Wirtgen ( 7 January 1848 , Koblenz -- 26 January 1924 , Bonn ) was a German pharmacist and botanist .

Albert Bartha de Nagyborosnyó ( 12 August 1877 - 2 December 1960 ) was a Hungarian military officer and politician , who served as Minister of Defence twice : in 1918 and , almost thirty years later , between 1946 and 1947 .

Henry John Horstman Fenton ( 18 February 1854 -- 13 January 1929 ) was a British chemist who , in the 1890s invented Fenton 's reagent , a solution of hydrogen peroxide and an iron catalyst that is used to oxidize contaminants or waste waters .

Alexander Gault MacGowan ( 7 February 1894 -- 30 November 1970 ) was a leading war correspondent during World War II . Born to Scottish parents in Manchester , England , he was educated at Manchester Grammar School .
Gao Bing ( 高棅 , 1350 to 1423 ) flourished during the newly established Ming Dynasty ( 1368 - -1644 ) as an author and poetry theorist .
Johannes Aanderaa ( 6 November 1927 -- 2 June 1991 ) was a Norwegian librarian , theatre critic , publisher and civil servant .
Sir William Derek Pattinson ( 31 March 1930 -- 10 October 2006 ) was Secretary - General of the General Synod of the Church of England from 1972 until 1990 .
Joseph Whipple , III ( 3 July 1725 - 1761 ) was a merchant in the Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations , and a Deputy Governor of the colony .
Martin Mehkek ( 7 August 1936 ; Novačka -- 1 July 2014 ; Koprivnica ) was a Croatian painter .
Wilson Earnshaw ( 20 September 1867 -- 24 November 1941 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played six matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1893 and 1896 .
Fabio Albarelli ( 26 June 1943 -- 4 October 1995 ) was an Italian competitive sailor .
Georgios Panou ( Greek : Γεώργιος Πάνου , 1770 -- 1 June 1863 ) was a Greek ship - owner , member of the Filiki Eteria , fighter and politician of the Greek War of Independence from Spetses .
Edgar Viies ( 12 January 1931 , Simititsa , Leningrad Oblast - 20 September 2006 ) was an Estonian sculptor .
Anders Rambech ( 2 September 1767 -- 14 September 1836 ) was a Norwegian district stipendiary magistrate and politician .
Giuseppe Bernardo Lecchi ( b. Felizzano 20 August 1895 - - d. Genoa 24 August 1967 ) was an Italian violin maker .
Muin Musavvir ( Persian : معین مصور‎ ) ( 1638 - -1697 ) was an Iranian painter .
Paul Heider ( 21 June 1868 -- 25 January 1936 ) was the 60 Grand Master of the Teutonic Order from 1933 to 1936 .
Rhoda Coffin , ( 1826 - -1909 ) , was a Quaker reformer .
Bernardo O'Connor y Ophaly , Spanish - Irish General , ( Strasbourg , 1696 - -1780 ) .
Alexander Minto Hughes ( 2 May 1945 -- 13 March 1998 ) , better known as Judge Dread , was an English reggae and ska musician .
Arthur Storer ( c. 1648 -- 1686 ) was America 's first colonial astronomer .
Andrew , Duke of Slavonia ( Hungarian : András szlavóniai herceg ; 1268 -- 1278 ) was the youngest son of King Stephen V of Hungary and his wife , Elizabeth the Cuman .
Raoul Hafner , ( 1905 - -1980 ) FEng , FRAes , was an Austrian - born British helicopter pioneer and engineer .
Mathias James O'Conway , aka Maitias O Conmhai ( 3 February 1766 -- 28 November 1842 ) was a linguist and lexicographer .
John Brislin ( May 12 , 1838- March 27 , 1907 ) was an American inventor who invented moveable rolling tables used for rolling large steel beams .
Edward Alexander Newell Arber ( 5 August 1870 , London - 14 June 1918 , Cambridge ) was an English botanist and paleontologist .
Sir John Beals Chandler ( 21 February 1887 -- 19 January 1962 ) was the Lord Mayor of Brisbane from 1940 to 1952 , and the Member for the Legislative Assembly of Queensland district of Hamilton from 1943 to 1947 .
Sir Adeyemo Alakija , KBE ( 25 May 1884 -- 1952 ) was a Nigerian lawyer , politician and businessman .
Terence Soall ( 22 March 1920 - 10 August 2006 ) was an English actor who appeared in numerous television productions over a 50-year period and in over 100 films .
Gideon Hausner ( Hebrew : גדעון האוזנר‎ , 26 September 1915 -- 15 November 1990 ) was an Israeli jurist and politician .
Annie Porter , married name Fantham ( 1880 - -8 May 1963 ) was an English zoologist and Honorary Parasitologist to the Zoological Society of London .
Karl Brandner ( 1898 - -1961 ) was born in Oak Park , Illinois and trained as an artist at the Art Institute of Chicago and the Chicago Fine Art Academy , Brander is best remembered as a regional artist who worked primarily in landscapes .
Lynn Caine ( 1924 - -1987 ) was an American author and publishing agent at Little , Brown and Company from 1967 to 1976 .
Franjo Kluz ( 19 September 1913 -- 14 September 1944 ) was a Yugoslav pilot from Bosnia and a People 's Hero of Yugoslavia .
Weng Tonghe ( Chinese : 翁同龢 ; pinyin : Wēng Tónghé ; Wade -- Giles : Weng T'ung - ho ; 1830 - -1904 ) , courtesy name Shuping ( 叔平 ) , was a Chinese Confucian scholar and imperial tutor who lived in the Qing dynasty .
Thomas Archer Hirst FRS ( 22 April 1830 -- 16 February 1892 ) was a 19th - century mathematician , specialising in geometry .
Mark Fredriksen ( 18 November 1936 -- 25 August 2011 ) was a French extreme right figure and the founder , in 1966 , of the neo - Nazi Fédération d'action nationaliste et européenne .
Archduke Joseph Ferdinand of Austria ( 24 May 1872 -- 28 August 1942 ) was an Austro - Hungarian Archduke and the titular Grand Duke of Tuscany from 17 January 1908 to 2 May 1921 , military commander , from 1916 Generaloberst , and early advocate of air power .
Roy Kellino ( 22 April 22 , 1912 -- 18 November 1956 ) was an English film director , producer and cinematographer .
Rolando Arcadio Masferrer Rojas ( 1918 - -1975 ) , born in Holguín , July 12 , 1918 , in former Oriente Province , better known simply as Rolando Masferrer , was a Cuban guerrilla leader , lawyer , congressman , newspaper publisher , member of the Cuban Communist Party and political activist .
Thomas Graham Howarth ( 15 February 1916 -- 8 April 2015 ) was an English entomologist of the National History Museum and Royal Army Medical Corps who spent three years as a Japanese prisoner during the Second World War , first at Changi and then at Jinsen in Korea .
Tomás Ó Dubhghaill ( ( ˈt̪ˠʊmˠaːsˠoːˈd̪ˠʊwəlʲ ) , born Thomas ( Tom ) Doyle ; 1917 -- 12 March 1962 ) was President of Sinn Féin from 1952 to 1954 and a Sinn Féin vice - president until his death .
Sir Gilbert Heathcote , 1st Baronet ( 2 January 1652 -- 25 January 1733 ) , was a Governor of the Bank of England and Lord Mayor of London in the early 18th Century .
Francis Samuel Williamson ( 18 January 1865 -- 6 February 1936 ) was an Australian poet who was published under the name Frank S. Williamson .
Professor Harold J. Grimm ( 1901 -- 1983 ) was an academic , historian and writer and an expert on the Reformation .
Gertrude Rhinelander Waldo ( c. 1837 -- May 27 , 1914 ) was an American heiress known for commissioning the Rhinelander Mansion located in Manhattan at 867 Madison Avenue on the south - east corner of 72nd Street , designed in the 1890s by Kimball & Thompson and completed in 1898 .
Frederick Foster Gough ( bapt . 7 February 1825 ; died 1 June 1889 ) was a Protestant Christian missionary who served with the Church Missionary Society during the late Qing Dynasty in China .
Eugene B. Van Camp ( March 31 , 1838 - June , 1904 ) was an espionage agent for the Confederate States of America during the American Civil War , assisting his father Dr. Aaron A. Van Camp in his spying activities .
Peter Benoit ( 17 August 1834 -- 8 March 1901 ) , was a Flemish composer of Belgian nationality .
Admiral George Vandeput ( Died 14 March 1800 ) was an English naval officer , the illegitimate son of Sir George Vandeput , 2nd Baronet ( c.1717 -- 17 June 1784 ) and an unknown mother .
Eagle of Delight , also called Hayne Hudjihini in Chiwere ( b. c. 1795 - d. 1822 ) , was one of the five wives of Chief Shaumonekusse of the Otoe tribe in the first quarter of the 19th century .
Basilio Repilado ( 4 March 1944 in Havana -- 4 December 2012 in Havana ) was a Cuban musician .
George Brodrick , 4th Viscount Midleton ( 1 November 1754 -- 12 August 1836 ) was a British nobleman .
Ymer Prizreni ( 1826−1887 ) was an Albanian political leader in the 19th century .
Bchira Ben Mrad ( بشيرة بن مراد ; 1993 - -1913 ) was a Tunisian women 's rights activist .
Antonio Benítez Fernández ( 2 June 1951 -- 19 February 2014 ) was a Spanish footballer who played as a left back .
Henri Grasso ( 1864 - -1944 ) was the son of Willem Grasso , founder of Grasso 's Royal Machine Factories Ltd. Henri was born to step in his father 's shoes .
Spencer Compton , 2nd Earl of Northampton ( May 1601 -- 19 March 1643 ) , styled Lord Compton from 1618 to 1630 , was an English soldier and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1621 to 1622 .
Hans Krumminga ( 6 May 1920 − 28 November 1943 ) was killed on 6 November 1943 , when straffed on take - off by 15 IAP Yakovlev Yak-1s led by Kpt Leontiy .
Noah Mann junior ( 1783 at Northchapel , Sussex -- 1825 in London ) was an English professional cricketer .
Franciszek Fesser ( born 16 August 1885 in Rogi , died 23 October 1956 in Piotrowice ( Katowice ) , was a Polish miner , union activist , Upper Silesian politician , insurgent , and deputy of the Silesian Parliament from 1930 - 1939 .
Aurore von Haxthausen ( Gustava Charlotta Märta Aurora : 1830 in Daretorp in Västergötland -- 7 February 1888 in Stockholm ) , known also by her artist pseudonym as Klara Kuhlman , was a Swedish author , composer , pianist and lady in waiting .
Paul Scriptoris ( c. 1460 -- October 21 , 1505 ) was a German Franciscan mathematician , Scotist , and professor at the University of Tübingen .
Diego Caballero ( died 1560 ) was a Spanish merchant and minor Conquistador in the Caribbean area and in the islands off the coast of Venezuela .
The Belgian born Émile Fernand - Dubois ( 1869 - -1952 ) was a sculptor and medallist .
Gao Kaidao ( 高開道 ) ( died 624 ) , at one point known as Li Kaidao ( 李開道 ) , was an agrarian rebel leader who rose against Sui Dynasty rule at the end of Emperor Yang 's reign .
Geirmund the Noisy ( died c. 978 ) was a Viking adventurer of the 10th century .
Ernest Frederick , Duke of Saxe - Coburg - Saalfeld ( Saalfeld , 8 March 1724 -- Coburg , 8 September 1800 ) , was a Duke of Saxe - Coburg - Saalfeld .
Ahtahkakoop ( Cree : Atāhkakohp , `` Starblanket'')(c . 1816 - -1896 ) was a Chief of the House Cree ( Wāskahikaniwiyiniwak ) division of the Plains Cree , who led his people through the difficult transition from hunter and warrior to farmer , and from traditional indigenous spiritualism to Christianity during the last third of the 19th century .
Ruaidri Ó Cellaigh ( died 1339 ) was King of Uí Maine and Chief of the Name .
Frank Broeze ( 18 August 1945 -- 4 April 2001 ) was a Professor of History at the University of Western Australia .
Mathilda Grabow ( 23 May 1852 -- 29 May 1940 ) , was a Swedish opera singer ( soprano ) .
Archie Skym ( 12 July 1906 -- 15 June 1970 ) was an international rugby union player for Wales and played club rugby for Llanelli and Cardiff .
Sebastian Aguilera de Heredia ( August 1561 -- 16 December 1627 ) was a Spanish monk , musician and composer .
John Swinfen ( 19 March 1613 -- 12 April 1694 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1645 and 1691 .
Jon Finch ( 2 March 1942 -- 28 December 2012 ) was an English actor who performed in many Shakespearean plays on stage , and made many films .
Edward Renz ( October 14 , 1891 -- March 1976 ) was an American racewalker .
James Clemens ( fl . 1750 - 1775 ) was a Liverpool , England merchant and shipowner , and Lord Mayor of Liverpool .
Pieter Groenhart ( February 21 , 1894 -- November 3 , 1965 ) was a Dutch lichenologist known for his research into tropical Asian lichens .
Jules White ( born Julius Weiss ) ( 17 September 1900 -- 30 April 1985 ) was a Hungarian - born American film director and producer best known for his short - subject comedies starring The Three Stooges .
Helmut Niedermeyer ( 28 February 1926 -- 3 February 2014 ) was an Austrian businessman and entrepreneur .
Robert Archibald Armstrong , LL.D. ( 1788 - -1867 ) , was a Gaelic lexicographer .
Walter Hough , Ph.D. ( 1859 - -1935 ) was an American ethnologist .
Ram Gopal Vijayvargiya ( 1905 -- 2003 ) was an Indian painter .
Herbert George Flaxman Spurrell ( 20 June 1877 -- 8 November 1918 ) , the biologist , physician and author , was the only son of the architect Herbert Spurrell and Harriet Rebecca Blaxland .
Burton Edward Livingston ( 1875 -- 1948 ) was an American plant physiologist , born at Grand Rapids , Michigan .
József Kürschák ( 14 March 1864 -- 26 March 1933 ) was a Hungarian mathematician noted for his work on trigonometry and for his creation of the theory of valuations .
Stephen III Báthory ( Hungarian : Báthory István ) ( died 11 November 1444 , Varna ) was a Hungarian nobleman and commander .
Edward C. Boyle ( died 1981 ) was the Allegheny County District Attorney in Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania from January 3 , 1956 until January 6 , 1964 .
Francis Edwardes ( died 15 December 1725 ) was a British Member of Parliament .
Kusaka Genzui ( 久坂 玄瑞 , 1840 -- 20 August 1864 ) was a samurai of the Japanese domain of Chōshū who was active during the Bakumatsu period and a key proponent of the sonnō jōi movement .
Antonio Siddi ( 16 June 1923 -- 21 January 1983 ) was an Italian athlete , who mainly competed in the 100 metres .
Khetcho ( Armenian : Խէչո ; 1872 -- July 1915 ) was a renowned Armenian activist and combatant .
The Moroccan Younis Mohammad Ibrahim al - Hayyari ( 1969 - -2005 ) was # 1 on Saudi Arabia 's list of 36 `` most wanted terrorist suspects '' published on 28 June 2005 .
Henri Christophe ( French pronunciation : ​(ɑ̃ʁi kʁistɔf ) ; 6 October 1767 -- 8 October 1820 ; used the anglicized version of Henry Christopher ) was a former slave of Bambara ethnicity , and key leader in the Haitian Revolution , which succeeded in gaining independence from France in 1804 .
Ellis Stones ( Ellis Andrew Stones , October 1 , 1895 -- April 9 , 1975 ) , was a constructor of private and public gardens -- many displaying naturalistic rockwork -- and a conservationist whose work and ideas profoundly influenced approaches to public landscaping in Australia .
Paul Curry ( 1917 - -1986 ) was the vice - president of the Blue Cross Insurance Company of New York , and a famous amateur magician who became well known in the magic community for inventing highly - original card magic .
Maria Flechtenmacher ( born Maria Mavrodin ; 1838 - -1888 ) was a Romanian writer , publicist and pedagogue , married to composer Alexandru Flechtenmacher .
Flavia Maxima Constantia ( 361/362 -- 383 ) was the first Empress consort of Gratian of the Western Roman Empire .
Mary Alment ( 9 April 1834 -- 11 April 1908 ) was a Northern Irish landscape and portrait artist .
Hannes Schmidhauser ( 9 September 1926 -- 29 January 2000 ) was a Swiss actor and footballer .
Wilhelm Schneemelcher ( Berlin 21 August 1914 -- 6 August 2003 in Bad Honnef ) was a German Protestant theologian and expert on the New Testament Apocrypha .
Govinda IV ( 930 - -935 CE ) was the younger brother of Amoghavarsha II . He became the Rashtrakuta emperor in 930 as described in the Kalasa record of Chikmagalur .
Emilio Polli ( 1901 - -1983 ) was an Italian swimmer .
Louis the Stammerer ( French : Louis le Bègue ) ( 1 November 846 -- 10 April 879 ) was the King of Aquitaine and later King of West Francia .

King Daemusin of Goguryeo ( 4 - 44 , r. 18 - 44 ) was the third ruler of Goguryeo , the northernmost of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .

Sir George Webbe Dasent ( 1817 - -1896 ) was a translator of folk tales and contributor to The Times .
Basil Hall Chamberlain ( 18 October 1850 -- 15 February 1935 ) was a professor of Japanese at Tokyo Imperial University and one of the foremost British Japanologists active in Japan during the late 19th century .

Stanley Berkeley ( 1855 - -1909 ) was an English painter of animal , sporting and historical subjects , especially military scenes .

Heulhae of Silla ( r. 310 - -356 , died 356 ) , titled Heulhae Isageum , was the sixteenth ruler of the Korean kingdom of Silla .
Frederick Thomas Bidlake ( June 1867 -- 17 September 1933 ) was an English racing cyclist of the late 19th century who became one of the most notable administrators of British road bicycle racing during the early 20th century .

Lawrence Kemys or Keymis ( died 1618 ) was a seaman and companion of Sir Walter Raleigh in his expeditions to Guiana in 1595 and 1617 - 18 .
Julian Nelson Frank ( 1906 - -1974 ) was a journalist , anti - communist , a special agent with U.S. Naval Intelligence , an investigator for the Senate Internal Security Subcommittee , and a bookstore owner .
