Nikiforos Vrettakos ( Greek : Νικηφόρος Βρεττάκος ; 1 January 1912 -- 4 August 1991 ) was a Greek writer and poet .
Egil Helle ( 28 April 1923 -- 2006 ) was a Norwegian newspaper editor , information worker and biographer .
Tine Debeljak ( 27 April 1903 -- 20 January 1989 ) was a Slovenian literary critic , translator , editor , and poet .
Wang Chengzong ( 王承宗 ) ( died 820 ) was a general of the Chinese Tang Dynasty who served a military governor ( Jiedushi ) of Chengde Circuit ( 成德 , headquartered in modern Shijiazhuang , Hebei ) .
Alene Lee ( 1931 - -1991 ) was an African - American member of the Beat generation in New York City whose romantic relationship with Jack Kerouac was the central theme in his novel The Subterraneans .
Judit Rumy de Rum et Rábadoroszló ( 11 January 1606 -- 1663 ) was a Hungarian noblewoman , wife of Dániel Esterházy , the founder of the Csesznek branch of the House of Esterházy .
Laimbu ( Manchu : ; Möllendorff : Laimbu ; Abkai : Laimbu ; 26 January 1612 - 23 June 1646 ) was a Manchu noble of the early Qing Dynasty .
Humphrey Cavell ( by 1525 - -1558 ) , was an English politician .
Dr George Darby Haviland ( 1857 - -1901 ) was a British surgeon and naturalist .
Giuseppe Sigismondo Ala Ponzone ( 21 March 1761 - 2 May 1842 ) was an Italian collector and entomologist .
Indubala Sukhadia(1 July 1921 -- 9 May 1999 ) , wife of late Mohanlal Sukhadia , was a social and political leader of Rajasthan .
John Argentine ( died 1507 ) was an English physician who attended Edward V of England and later Arthur , Prince of Wales , and was Provost of King 's College , Cambridge .
Sir Geoffrey Summers , 1st Baronet CBE , DL , JP , CStJ ( 2 September 1891 -- 17 January 1972 ) , was a British businessman .
Saintin de Meaux ( or Saint Santin also known as Saint Sanctin , fr . Saint - Santin de Meaux , lat . Sanctinus , c. 270 - 356 , Meaux ) was a French bishop and missionary .
Uqba ibn Abu Mu'ayt ( Arabic : عقبة بن أبو معيط‎ ) ( died 624 ) was one of the principal adversaries of Islam .
Thomas Fane , 8th Earl of Westmorland ( March 1701 -- 25 November 1771 ) , MP for Lyme Regis and a lord commissioner of trade .
Allen Edward Everitt ( 1824 -- 11 June 1882 ) was an English architectural artist and illustrator .
Deacon Chiu Te - ken , JP ( Chinese : 邱德根 ; 1 May 1924 -- 17 March 2015 ) was a Hong Kong entrepreneur .
Pagolo Arsago ( died 1563 ) was a member of the Goldsmith 's Guild .
Donald Macaulay , Baron Macaulay of Bragar , QC ( 14 November 1933 -- 12 June 2014 ) was a British Labour politician and member of the House of Lords .
Dimitar Kondovski ( Macedonian : Димитар Кондовски ) ( 1927 - 1993 ) was a Macedonian painter , critic and professor .
William Samuel Jones ( May 28 , 1920 -- November 15 , 2007 ) was a Welsh language author , playwright and scriptwriter better known as W. S. Jones or Wil Sam .
Thoralf Strømstad ( 13 January 1897 -- 10 January 1984 ) was a Norwegian Nordic skier who was awarded the Holmenkollen medal in 1923 .
Joseph McKenzie ( 19 March 1929 -- 5 July 2015 ) was a Scottish photographer known as the `` father of modern Scottish photography '' .
Robert Caswell ( 13 July 1946 - 29 October 2006 ) was an Australian screenwriter of films and television .
Sándor Bejczy ( 1920 - -2004 ) was a Hungarian politician , member of the National Assembly ( MP ) from FKGP National List between 1990 and 1994 .
Amadeus Aba or Amade Aba ( Hungarian : Aba Amadé ; ? -- 5 September 1311 ) was a Hungarian oligarch in the Kingdom of Hungary who ruled de facto independently the northern and north - eastern counties of the kingdom ( today parts of Hungary , Slovakia and Ukraine ) .
Rinaldo degli Albizzi ( 1370 - -1442 ) was an Italian nobleman , a member of the Florentine family of the Albizzi .
Walter Franklyn Barrett ( 1873 -- 16 July 1964 ) , better known as Franklyn Barrett , was an Australian film director and cinematographer .
Sallustius Lucullus ( d. c. 89 ) was a governor of Roman Britain during the late 1st century , holding office after Gnaeus Julius Agricola although it is unclear whether he directly inherited the post or if there was another unknown governor in between .
Henry James Richter ( 1772 - -1857 ) , artist and philosopher , was born in Middlesex , possibly at 40 Great Newport Street , Soho , on 8 March 1772 and baptised at St Anne 's Church , Soho , on 5 April at that same year .
Leonhard Schiemer ( c. 1500 -- 14 January 1528 ) was an early pacifist Anabaptist writer and martyr whose work survives in the Ausbund .
Lieutenant Colonel William Gordon Perrin , OBE ( 1874 - -1931 ) was an R.A.F. and Navy officer , and the Admiralty librarian from 1908 to 1931 .
Gerhard I , Count of Holstein - Itzehoe ( 1232 -- 21 December 1290 ) was the only count of Holstein - Itzehoe .
Niccolò Gualtieri ( 9 July 1688 -- 15 February 1744 ) was an Italian doctor and malacologist .
Thomas Christian ( 1754 - -1828 ) was the translator of John Milton 's Paradise Lost into Manx , an author of Manx carols , and vicar of Marown parish , Isle of Man .
Vrindavana Dasa Thakura or Brindaban Das ( 1507 - 1589 CE ) was the author of the Chaitanya Bhagavata , the first full - length biography of Chaitanya Mahaprabhu written in the Bengali language .
John Cennick ( 12 December 1718 -- 4 July 1755 ) was an early Methodist and Moravian evangelist and hymnwriter .
Stańczyk ( c. 1480 - -1560 ) ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈstaɲt͡ʂɨk ) ) was the most famous court jester in Polish history .
George Lewis Becke ( or Louis Becke ; 18 June 1855 -- 18 February 1913 ) was an Australian Pacific trader , short - story writer and novelist .
Johann Samuel Drese ( c. 1644 -- 1 December 1716 ) was a German composer and member of the musical Drese family .
Étienne Jacob ( c. 1648 -- 1726 ) was a Canadian court officer , sergeant of the Sovereign Council of New France , seigneurial notary and a judge of the bailiff 's court of Beaupré and Île d'Orléans .
William Alexander Young MB , CHB , DPH , DTM ( 5 November 1889 -- 28 May 1928 ) was a Scottish doctor and surgeon who specialised in tropical medicine .
Marmaduke Stone ( 28 November 1748 -- 22 August 1834 ) was an English Jesuit , in a position of leadership when the Order was dissolved .
David Pears ( 8 August 1921 -- 1 July 2009 ) was a British philosopher renowned for his work on Ludwig Wittgenstein .
Joseph Kenny Meadows , ( November 1790 - -August 1874 ) better known as Kenny Meadows , was a British caricaturist and illustrator .
Razadarit ( Burmese : ရာဇာဓိရာဇ် ( jàza̰dəɹɪ̀ʔ ) ; Thai : ราชาธิราช , rtgs : Rachathirat ; Sanskrit : राजाधिराज Rājādhirāja `` King of Kings '' ; 1368 - -1421 ) was the ninth king of the Hanthawaddy Pegu Kingdom in Burma from 1384 to 1421 .
Ditmar Meidell ( 24 January 1826 -- 13 July 1900 ) is a Norwegian magazine and newspaper editor .
Tony Kellow ( 1 May 1952 -- 20 February 2011 ) was an English professional footballer .
Martin Copley ( 1940 -- 30 July 2014 ) was a British - born Australian conservationist and philanthropist who established the Australian Wildlife Conservancy ( AWC ) , an organisation which purchases and manages large areas of land , mainly former pastoral properties , as nature reserves ( called ' sanctuaries ' ) for the conservation of biodiversity .
Evo Anton DeConcini ( March 25 , 1901 -- 1986 ) was Attorney General of Arizona , and a Justice of the Arizona Supreme Court from 1949 to 1953 .
Sidney Greenberg ( September 27 , 1917 -- March 31 , 2003 ) was an American rabbi and author .
Magdalo Mussio ( 1925 - -12 August 2006 ) was an Italian author , artist , animator and editor .
Gilbert Ashton MC ( 27 September 1896 -- 6 February 1981 ) was an English cricketer who played 62 first - class matches between the wars , mostly for Cambridge University ( whom he captained in 1921 , and also captained at football ) and Worcestershire .
Maharaja Sir Rameshwar Singh Thakur Bahadur GCIE KCB ( 16 January 1860 -- 3 July 1929 ) was the Maharaja of Darbhanga from 1898 to his death .
Justice William Alfred Wearing QC ( 12 November 1816 -- 24 February 1875 ) was a prominent jurist in the Colony of South Australia , who lost his life in the wreck of S.S. Gothenburg
Saint Ampelus ( died 302 ) is a martyr venerated by the Eastern Orthodox and Roman Catholic churches .
John Byron , 1st Baron Byron ( 1599 , Newstead , Nottinghamshire -- 23 August 1652 ) was an English Royalist and supporter of Charles I during the English Civil War .
Murray Nicoll ( 20 July 1943 -- 2 May 2010 ) was an Australian journalist and broadcaster whose career spanned more than 45 years .
Margrete Aamot Øverland ( 11 February 1913 - 1978 ) was a Norwegian resistance member during the Second World War , and later editor of the Riksmål newspaper Frisprog .
Lin Xu ( 1875 -- 28 September 1898 ) , courtesy name Tungu ( 暾谷 ) , was a Chinese politician , scholar , songwriter and poet who lived in the late Qing dynasty .
Luís do Rego Barreto , Viscount Geraz Lima , ( 28 October 1777 , Viana do Castelo - 7 September 1840 , Vila Real ) better known as General Luis Rego , was a military and Portuguese colonial administrator who distinguished himself in the fight against the French invasion .
Leonard MacClain ( September 8 , 1899 , Philadelphia , Pennsylvania -- September 1967 , Devault , Pennsylvania ) was an American keyboardist and composer who was prominent as an organist in the Philadelphia area .
Giuseppa Iolanda Menichelli ( 10 January 1890 -- 29 August 1984 ) , known as Pina Menichelli , was an Italian actress and silent film star .
Katharine Coman ( 23 November 1857 -- 11 January 1915 ) was an American social activist and economist .
Arthur Bertram St Hill ( 1872 - 25 August 1911 ) was an early cricketer in the West Indies .
Fatima Soltan ( died 1681 ) was the last khanbika ( queen ) of Qasim Khanate ( 1679 - -81 ) .
Hong Chengchou ( 1593 - -1665 ) , courtesy name Yanyan and art name Hengjiu , was a Chinese official who served under the Ming and Qing dynasties .
Sir Edward Anwyl ( 5 August 1866 -- 8 August 1914 ) was a Welsh academic , specializing in the Celtic languages .
Roger Scott ( 23 October 1943 -- 31 October 1989 ) was a British radio disc jockey .
Nguyễn Cửu Đàm ( died 1777 ) was a Vietnamese general under the Nguyễn lords who built the citadel in Saigon in 1772 to protect the newly acquired southern territories against the Siamese army .
Hormizd IV ( Middle Persian : 𐭠𐭥𐭧𐭥𐭬𐭦𐭣 ; New Persian : هرمز چهارم ) , was king of the Sasanian Empire from 579 to 590 .
Frederik Alexander Adolf Gregory ( Doesburg , 13 May 1814 - ' s - Gravenhage , 16 July 1891 ) was a Dutch viceadmiraal .
David Lindo Alexander ( 5 October 1842 in the City of London -- 1922 ) was an English barrister and Jewish community leader .
Louis Dominique Girard ( 1815- Paris , 1871 ) was a French hydraulic engineer .
Charles - Édouard Brown - Séquard FRS ( 8 April 1817 -- 2 April 1894 ) , also known as Charles Edward , was a Mauritian physiologist and neurologist who , in 1850 , became the first to describe what is now called Brown - Séquard syndrome .
John Skirrow Wright ( 1822 -- 15 April 1880 ) was one of the prominent pioneers and social improvers of the 19th century in Birmingham , England ; and inventor of the Postal Order .
The Rt Rev Thomas Dealtry ( 1795 - 1861 ) was an Anglican Bishop in the 19th century .
Kenny Craddock ( 18 April 1950 - 30 May 2002 ) was an instrumentalist , composer and producer .
Joseph - A. Fowler ( 14 November 1845 -- 4 January 1917 ) was a Canadian composer , organist , choirmaster , pianist , and music educator .
Isidore Isaac Hirschman , Jr. ( 1922 - 1990 ) was an American mathematician at Washington University in St. Louis working on analysis .
Maria Cristina of Naples and Sicily ( Maria Cristina Amelia Teresa ; 17 January 1779 -- 11 March 1849 ) was a Princess of Naples and Sicily and later Queen of Sardinia as wife of King Charles Felix .
Charles von Hügel ( born Carl Alexander Anselm Baron von Hügel ; 25 April 1795 -- 2 June 1870 ) was an Austrian noble , army officer , diplomat , botanist , and explorer , now primarily remembered for his travels in northern India during the 1830s .
Osbert Parsley ( 1511 -- 1585 ) was an English renaissance composer .
Henry White Warren ( 1831 - -1912 ) was an American Methodist Episcopal bishop and author , brother of William Fairfield Warren .
Björn Hjörtur Guðmundsson ( 14 January 1911 -- 14 July 1998 ) , also known as Bjössi , was an Icelandic craftsman , master carpenter , idealist and environmental pioneer .
Jane Chabria ( 1940 - -2004 ) was an education pioneer in Columbus , Ohio .
Kakeda Toshimune ( died 1548 ) was a Japanese samurai of the Sengoku period , who served the Date clan .
James Verne Dusenberry ( 7 April 1906 -- 16 December 1966 ) was well educated and a publicly acclaimed scholar .
Beate Hermelin , affectionately known as Ati , ( 7 August 1919 -- 14 January 2007 ) was a German - born Experimental Psychologist , who worked in the UK and was a pioneer in the experimental study of autism .
Adolf Streckeisen ( 1857 - 1916 ) was professor of medicine at Basel University , first forensic physician ( Gerichtsarzt ) of Basel ( a post created in 1895 ) and president of the Basel Mission .
Ridgwell Cullum ( pseudonym of Sidney Groves Burghard ) ( 13 August 1867 -- 3 November 1943 ) was a British writer who wrote a large number of adventure novels over more than 30 years , usually set in sparsely populated regions of the USA or Canada .
John de Courcy ( also John de Courci ) ( 1150 - -1219 ) was an Anglo - Norman knight who arrived in Ireland in 1176 .
Datuk Seri Dr. Burhanuddin bin Muhammad Nur al - Hilmi , commonly known as Burhanuddin al - Helmy ( 1911 - -6 November 1969 ) was a Malaysian politician .
Georgije Magarašević ( Adaševci , 10 September 1793 -- Novi Sad , 6 January 1830 ) , Serbian writer , historian , editor and publisher , dramatist , translator and collector of folk proverbs .
Eric Lloyd Williams ( 1915 - -1988 ) was a South African - born journalist and war correspondent who covered World War II for the South African Press Association and Reuters .
Henry Shalofsky , better known as Hank Shaw ( 23 June 1926 -- 26 October 2006 ) was an English bebop jazz trumpeter .
Beatrix Havergal ( 1901 - 1980 ) was an English horticulturist .
Prof John Kaye Charlesworth FRSE FRGS FGS CBE ( 1889 - 1972 ) was a British geologist and academic author .
Joseph Baggaley ( c. 1884 -- 19 October 1918 ) was a trade unionist , born in England , who came to Regina , Saskatchewan , Canada with his wife and four children in 1911 .
Robert Louden ( died 1867 ) was a Confederate messenger and partisan in the American Civil War .
Johan Andreas Hallén ( 22 December 1846 -- 11 March 1925 ) was a Swedish Romantic composer , conductor and music teacher , primarily known for his operas , which were heavily influenced by Richard Wagner 's music dramas .
Peter Bander van Duren ( Cologne , 30 July 1930 -- 21 April 2004 ) was a British writer on heraldry and orders of knighthood .
Lauri Nissinen ( 31 July 1918 in Joensuu - 17 June 1944 in Kaukjärvi ) was a World War II flying ace in the Finnish Air Force .
Sir Ernest Gray ( 27 August 1856 -- 6 May 1932 ) was a British educational reformer and Conservative politician .
Sir John Cordell , 3rd Baronet ( baptized 11 November 1677-died 8 May 1704 ) was an English politician .
Pedro de Atarés ( c. 1083 , Borja -- 21 February 1151 ) was a Spanish noble and member of the House of Aragón .
Vincenzo Catena ( c. 1470 -- 1531 ) was an Italian painter of the Renaissance Venetian school .
Ladislav Kralj - Međimurec ( Čakovec , 24 April 1891 -- 9 February 1976 ) was a Croatian painter and engraver .
William Thomas Oldrieve ( 15 December 1853 -- 12 January 1922 ) was a British architect and scholar primarily associated with public buildings in his role as Architect for Scotland within the Office of Works .
Cyril Harcourt ( 1872 - -1924 ) was a noted writer for the London and New York stages who appeared in his own plays .
Alfons Spielhoff ( July 3 , 1912 -- December 9 , 1987 ) was a German politician , serving as minister of cultural affairs for Dortmund in the 1970s .
Charles François Duhoux d'Hauterive ( 13 August 1736 -- May 1799 ) fought in the War of the Austrian Succession and Seven Years ' War , rising in rank to become a lieutenant colonel of cavalry .
Paul Hausser ( 7 October 1880 -- 21 December 1972 ) was an officer in the German Army , achieving the rank of lieutenant - general in the inter - war Reichswehr .
Major General Sir Michael O'Moore Creagh KBE , MC ( 16 May 1892 -- 1970 ) was a British soldier who served in both the First and Second World Wars .
Galeazzo I Visconti ( 21 January 1277 -- 6 August 1328 ) was lord of Milan from 1322 to 1327 .
Giles Strangways ( 3 June 1615 -- 20 July 1675 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1640 and 1675 .
Wamsutta ( c.1634 - -1662 ) , also known as Alexander Pokanoket , as he was called by New England colonists , was the eldest son of Massasoit ( meaning Great Leader ) Ousa Mequin of the Pokanoket Tribe and Wampanoag nation .
Anna Sprengel ( allegedly died in 1891 ) , countess of Landsfeldt , love - child of Ludwig I of Bavaria and Lola Montez , is a person whose existence was never proven , and who it now seems was invented by William Wynn Westcott to confer legitimacy on the Golden Dawn .
Rev. Samuel Spring ( 1746 - -1819 ) was an early American Revolutionary War chaplain and Congregationalist minister .
Vladimir Kren ( 8 December 1903 -- 2 December 1948 ) was a Croatian major general and commander of the Air Force of the Independent State of Croatia ( ZNDH ) during World War II . He was an officer in the Royal Yugoslav Air Force ( VVKJ ) before the war .
Peter de Leia , O.S.B. ( died 16 July 1198 ) , was Bishop of St David 's from 1176 until his death .
Robert D. Kohn ( 1870 - 1953 ) was an American architect most active in New York City .
Juan Luis de Camarena ( d. 1642 ) was a Spanish soldier and colonial administrator who was governor of the Province of Margarita from 18 February 1638 until 1642 .
Sir William Talbot , 1st Baronet ( died 16 March 1633 ) , was an Irish lawyer and politician .
Karl Rudolph Koenig ( German : Rudolf Koenig ; 26 November 1832 -- 2 October 1901 ) , known by himself and others as Rudolph Koenig , was a German physicist , chiefly concerned with acoustic phenomena .
General Sir Anthony Farrington , 1st Baronet ( 6 February 1742 - -3 November 1823 ) was a British Army officer of the Royal Artillery .
Evan Tom Davies ( 24 September 1904 -- 8 October 1973 ) was a Welsh mathematician and linguist .
Imre Sulyok de Lekcse et Alsószopor ( ? -- 25 January 1578 ) was a Hungarian politician in the Principality of Transylvania , who served as Chancellor of Transylvania from 1576 until his death .
Frank Sayers ( 1763 - -1817 ) was an English poet and metaphysical writer .
Matsunobori Shigeo ( 20 July 1924 - 21 April 1986 ) was a sumo wrestler from Matsudo Chiba , Japan .
Konstantinos Zappas ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Ζάππας 1814 - -1892 ) was a Greek entrepreneur and national benefactor .
Liu Qiong ( Chinese : 刘琼 ) ( 1913 - -2002 ) was a Chinese film director and actor .
Filippo Bigioli ( San Severino Marche , June 4 , 1798 - 1878 ) was an Italian painter , active in a late neoclassical style
Juan García de Salazar ( 12 February 1639 ( baptized ) -- 8 July 1710 ) was a Spanish baroque composer best remembered for his choral works in the stile antico , though a few Spanish works in a more modern style have also survived .
Lew Bradford ( 24 December 1916 -- 1984 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a centre half .
John Davies Gilbert ( 5 December 1811 -- 16 April 1854 ) was a land owner , born in Eastbourne the son of Davies Gilbert and Mary Ann Gilbert .
Alfred Benjamin Butts ( 1890 -- 1962 ) was an American political scientist and university administrator .
Jacob Groenewegen ( died 22 May 1609 ) was a Dutch merchant , who was the leading merchant ( opperkoopman ) on the fleet under Pieter Willemsz .
Sir Robert John Price ( 26 April 1854 -- 18 April 1926 ) was a British surgeon , barrister and Liberal Party politician .
Thomas John Newbold ( 8 February 1807 -- 29 May 1850 ) was an English soldier in the service of the East India Company , known as a traveller and orientalist .
Charles Courant ( 14 April 1896 -- 26 June 1982 ) was a Swiss freestyle wrestler and Olympic medalist .
John Scott Porter ( 1801 - -1880 ) was an Irish biblical scholar and Unitarian minister .
Benjamin Briscoe ( May 1867 - -26 June 1945 ) was born in Detroit , Michigan , and was an automobile pioneer and industrialist .
Sejdo Bajramović ( 1927 - -1993 ) was a Yugoslav soldier and politician of the former Yugoslavia , who was the acting head of state of Yugoslavia for a brief time in 1991 .
Jan Tesánek ( Latin : Joannis Tessanek ) ( 1728 - -1788 ) was a Bohemian scholar and author of scientific literature .
Mikhail Vasilyevich Bocharov ( Russian : Михаил Васильевич Бочаров , 1872 -- 29 April 1936 ) was a Russian opera singer .
Cornelius Bongey ( or Bungey ) ( died 19 September 1555 ) was an English Protestant martyr who was burnt at Coventry in September 1555 .
Robert Thistlethwayte ( baptized 16 December 1690 -- c. January , 1744 ) was a Warden of Wadham College , Oxford and clergyman in the Church of England .
João Lourenço Rebelo died at Apelação ( Loures ) on 16 November 1661 .
Frances Tipton Hunter ( 1896 - -1957 ) was an illustrator who created covers for The Saturday Evening Post and many other magazines between the 1920s and 1950s .
Abbad ibn Bishr ( Arabic : عباد بن بشر‎ ) ( c.606 - -632 ) was a companion of the Islamic prophet Muhammad .
Jean - Paul Hétu ( 1932 -- 30 July 2012 ) was a Quebec trade unionist .
Félicien Henry Caignart de Saulcy ( 1832 - 1912 ) was a French entomologist specialising in Coleoptera .
Giovanni Fouchetti ( 1757 - 1789 ) published one of the earliest method books for the mandolin , c. 1771 .
Dasarathi Tah ( 1911 - -1980 ) was a politician and journalist in the Indian state of West Bengal .
Kathleen Haddon ( 1888 - 1961 ) was an English zoologist , photographer , and scholar of string - figures .
Joseph Kincaid MICE ( 1834 - 1907 ) was an engineer responsible for the construction of a significant number of tramways in Great Britain .
Roger Montgomery ( 1925 - -2003 ) was an American architect , and Professor at Washington University in St. Louis .
Bienvenido Granda , born Rosendo Bienvenido Granda Aguilera ( Havana , August 30 , 1915 - Mexico City , July 9 , 1983 ) , was a Cuban vocalist / musician , singing boleros , son montunos , guarachas and other Cuban rhythms .
Alan Pentland ( 3 October 1883 -- 15 December 1952 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Thomas Gerard , 1st Baronet ( 1560 -- 16 February 1621 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1597 and 1621 .
Newman E. Drake ( 16 December 1860 -- 17 March 1930 ) was an American entrepreneur and philanthropist who founded Drake 's , an American baking company now owned by McKee Foods
Lodowicke Muggleton ( 1609 - -1698 ) was an English plebeian religious thinker , who gave his name to Muggletonianism .
Hunsur Krishnamurthy ( 9 February 1914 -- 13 February 1989 ) was an Indian playwright , film director , producer , actor , screenwriter and lyricist in Kannada cinema .
Émile Zermani , ( 25 September 1911 -- 10 May 1983 ) was a French football player .
Sir Richard Garth PC QC ( 11 May 1820 -- 23 March 1903 ) was Member of Parliament for Guildford from 1866 to 1868 and Chief Justice of Bengal from 1875 to 1886 .
Francis Otto , Duke of Brunswick - Lüneburg ( 1530 - -1559 ) was the Prince of Lüneburg from 1555 to 1559 .
Bernard Codd ( d. 29 July 2013 , aged 79 ) was an English professional motorcycle road racer .
Gibson Nyandoro ( born in 1954 or 1955 , died in 2008 ) was a Zimbabwean war veteran and political dissident who died in military custody in Zimbabwe in May 2008 .
Sri Prakasa ( 3 August 1890 -- 23 June 1971 ) was an Indian politician , freedom - fighter and administrator .
Victor Jacobi , Jakobi Viktor ( 22 October 1883 -- 10 December 1921 ) was a Hungarian operetta composer .
Sir Rubert William Boyce ( 22 April 1863 -- 16 June 1911 ) was an English pathologist and hygienist , known for his work on tropical medicine .
William Alder Strange ( 1813 -- 1874 ) was a headmaster and author .
Blessed John Larke ( died 7 March 1544 ) was an English priest and martyr , who was executed during the reign of Henry VIII . He was a personal friend of Thomas More .
Zhang Tianran ( 張天然 ) ( 8 August 1889 -- 29 September 1947 ) was the eighteenth patriarch as well as the founder of the I - Kuan Tao religious sect .
Otto Liebermann ( 24 November 1898 - 6 April 1974 ) was a chemist who invented a synthesis of dolomite .
Sir Charles Hanbury Williams , KB ( 8 December 1708 -- 2 November 1759 ) was a Welsh diplomat , writer and satirist .
H. H. Swami Santhananda Saraswati Avadhoota Swamigal ( 28 March 1921 - 27 May 2002 ) born as Subrahmanyam was a Hindu spiritual leader and teacher who established the worship of Devi Bhuvaneswari in Tamil Nadu .
Peter K. Palangyo ( 1939 - 18 January 1993 ) was a Tanzanian novelist and diplomat .
William H. Sylvis ( 1828 - -1869 ) was a pioneer American trade union leader .
Colonel Humphrey Mews ( 1941 - 1990 ) was Deputy Private Secretary to His Royal Highness the Prince of Wales 1986 - 1988 .
Pierre Gaspard Marie Grimod d'Orsay ( 14 December 1748 -- 3 January 1809 , Vienna ) , comte d'Orsay , was a collector of sculptures , paintings and drawings ( which he left to the Louvre ) .
Winslow Lewis ( 1770 - -1850 ) was a sea captain , engineer , inventor and contractor active in the construction of many American lighthouses during the first half of the nineteenth century .
Sir Richard Aluwihare , KCMG , CBE , CCS , JP ( 23 May 1895 -- 22 December 1976 ) was a Sri Lankan civil servant and diplomat .
Mailin mac Tanaide Ó Maolconaire , Ollamh Síol Muireadaigh , c.1360 - 1441 .
Rothari ( or Rothair ) , ( c. 606 -- 652 ) , of the house of Arodus , was king of the Lombards from 636 to 652 ; previously he had been duke of Brescia .
Józef Chaciński ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈjuzɛf xaˈt͡ɕiɲskʲi ) ; 13 March 1889 , Warsaw -- 6 May 1954 , Góra Kalwaria ) was a Polish lawyer and politician .
Arthur Douglas Peppercorn ( 28 February 1847 - 1926 ) was a London - born landscape painter who has been likened to Corot .
Dennis Hargrove Cooke ( February 23 , 1904 -- March 1982 ) was the fourth president of what is now East Carolina University .
Sefer Reis ( Ottoman Turkish:سفر ) ( died 1565 ) was a Turkish privateer and Ottoman admiral who was active against the Portuguese in the Indian Ocean in the 16th century .
Paulus Verschuur ( 1606 -- 1667 ) , was a Dutch mayor of Rotterdam , known today for his portrait by Frans Hals .
Gerrard Andrewes ( 1750 - -1825 ) was an English churchman , Dean of Canterbury from 1809 .
Emile Bernheim ( 1886 -- 1985 ) was a Belgian industrialist .
Ahmad ibn Tawoos ( Arabic : أحمد بن طاووس‎ ) , also known as `` Tawoos '' or `` al - Taus '' ( died 673 ) , was one of the Tabi``in , and one of the narrators of hadith .
Giuseppe Torelli ( 22 April 1658 -- 8 February 1709 ) was an Italian violist , violinist , teacher , and composer .
Pribislav - Henry ( German : Pribislaw - Heinrich ; d. 1150 ) was a Slavic Christian prince and the last ruler of the Hevelli ( Stodorani ) tribe in the Northern March of Brandenburg .
Sir Giles Rolls Loder , 3rd Baronet ( 1914 - -1999 ) was an English aristocrat , WWII veteran , public official , horticulturalist and yachtsman .
Islwyn Ffowc Elis ( Welsh pronunciation : ( ˈɪslʊɨn foʊk ˈɛlɪs ) ; 17 November 1924 -- 22 January 2004 ) was one of Wales 's most popular Welsh - language writers .
Adriaan Pauw , knight , heer van Heemstede , Bennebroek , Nieuwerkerk etc . ( 1 November 1585 -- 21 February 1653 ) was Grand Pensionary of Holland from 1631 to 1636 and from 1651 to 1653 .
Sarah Maria Wilson ( died 1786 ) was an English actress .
Hazrat Khwaja Syed Mohammad Badshah Qadri - ul - Chishti Yamani Raichuri Rahmatullah'alaih ( 1903 ( 1324 Hijri ) -- 1978 ) , was a Sufi saint of the Chisti order in India , known commonly as Badshah Quadri or Badesha Qadri , who preached universal brotherhood and peace .
Ken Ogata ( 緒形拳 Ogata Ken ; 20 July 1937 -- 5 October 2008 ) was a Japanese actor .
Andy Cowie ( 11 March 1913 -- 1972 ) was a professional footballer who played for Dundee , Aberdeen and Swindon Town .
Ralph Stob ( 1894 -- 1965 ) was an educator , academic , and former president of Calvin College in Grand Rapids , Michigan .
Susan Feilding , Countess of Denbigh ( née Villiers ; 1583 -- 1652 ) was an English courtier .
Jayakant Mishra ( 20 November 1922 -- 3 February 2009 ) was an Indian scholar and author .
Anthony Tuckney ( September 1599 , Kirton - in - Holland -- February 1670 ) was an English Puritan theologian and scholar .
John Every ( c 1643 - 1679 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1679 .
Dixon Edward Hoste ( 23 July 1861 -- 11 May 1946 ) was a British Protestant Christian missionary to China and the longest lived of the Cambridge Seven and successor to James Hudson Taylor as General Director of the China Inland Mission , ( from 1902 to 1935 ) .
Isaac Habrecht II ( 1589 - 1633 ) was a professor of astronomy and mathematics in Strasbourg .
Wrisley Brown ( 1883 - 1943 ) was Washington , DC lawyer and a soldier .
Joan Winfield ( 24 September 1918 -- 16 June 1978 ) was an Australian - born actress and talented violinist , who appeared in Hollywood films in the 1940s , mostly in uncredited roles .
Lloyd Kenyon , 3rd Baron Kenyon ( 1 April 1805 -- 14 July 1869 ) , was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Yudhvir Singh ( Hindi : युद्धवीर सिंह , b. 1897 , Jaipur , d. 1983 , New Delhi ) was an Indian freedom fighter , politician and homeopathic doctor .
James Gordon Melville Turner GC ( 1907 - 5 November 1967 ) was a British merchant seaman .
Gabriel von Seidl ( 9 December 1848 -- 27 April 1913 ) was a German architect and a representative of the historicist style of architecture .
Oda of Haldensleben ( ca . 955/60 -- 1023 ) was a German noblewoman and by marriage Duchess of the Polans .
Ernst Leopold Prinz von Sachsen - Coburg und Gotha ( Ernst Leopold Eduard Wilhelm Josias ; 14 January 1935 -- 27 June 1996 ) was the elder son of Johann Leopold , Hereditary Prince of Saxe - Coburg and Gotha and Baroness Feodora von der Horst .
Joe Brophy ( 5 April 1890 -- 25 September 1972 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Niketas Triphyllios ( Greek : Νικήτας Τριφύλλιος , died 30 April 803 ) was one of the highest officials of the Byzantine Empire during the reign of Byzantine empress Irene of Athens ( 797 - -802 ) , holding the position of Domestic of the Schools .
Thomas Wrightington ( c. 1797 - -July 8 , 1853 ) was an early settler of San Diego , California .
Epiphanius of Pavia ( 438 - -496 ) , later venerated as Saint Epiphanius of Pavia , was Bishop of Pavia from 466 until his death in 496 .
Dr. Albert Plesman ( 7 September 1889 -- 31 December 1953 ) was a Dutch pioneer in aviation and the first president of KLM , the oldest airline in the world still operating under its original name .
Arthur Ashley Sykes ( 1684 - -1756 ) was an Anglican religious writer , known as an inveterate controversialist .
Dr. Rudolphina Menzel ( 1891 - -1973 ) was a cynologist , best known for her work in the field of animal behavior , from Vienna , Austria .
Sven Roger Blomquist ( 25 September 1956 -- 15 September 2014 ) was a Swedish sports journalist , working for state broadcaster SVT .
Lilian Doris Thompson MBE OBE ( née Bean ; 12 January 1903 -- 23 June 2004 ) was a British businessperson who was the managing director and chairman of Blackpool Pleasure Beach .
Stella Sutherland ( 7 October 1924 -- 15 October 2015 ) was one of the prominent Shetland writers of the later 20th and early 21st century .
Jasodhara Bagchi ( born 1937 in Kolkata -- 9 January 2015 ) was a leading Indian feminist critic and activist .
Dov Karmi ( Hebrew : דב כרמי‎ ; ‎1905 -- 14 May 1962 ) was a renowned Israeli architect of the pre - statehood era .
Theophilus Cazenove , or Theophile Cazenove ( 13 October 1740 -- 6 March 1811 ) , was a Dutch financier and one of the agents of the Holland Land Company .
Bartholomew Newsam ( died 1593 ) , was clockmaker to Queen Elizabeth I , probably born at York .
Bill Raidler , known as `` Little Bill '' Raidler ( 1870 ? - 1904 ) was an outlaw of the Old West , and member of the Doolin - Dalton gang .
Fleetwood Churchill M.D. ( 1808 - -1878 ) was an English physician , known as an obstetrician and medical writer .
Gustav Sule ( 10 September 1910 -- 3 April 1942 ) was an Estonian javelin thrower .
John Newton Waddel ( born Willington , South Carolina , April 2 , 1812 ; died 1895 ) was the Chancellor of the University of Mississippi from 1865 to 1874 .
John William Kitson ( 1846 -- February 1888 ) was an English - born architectural sculptor who worked in the United States .
Harry Fenn ( 1837 -- April 22 , 1911 ) was an English - born American illustrator , landscape painter , etcher , and wood engraver .
Kanō Naonobu ( 狩野 尚信 , 25 November 1607 -- 7 May 1650 ) was a Japanese painter of the Kanō school of painting during the early Edo period .
Christopher T. Gonzalez , also known as Chris Gonzalez , was an activist who succumbed to AIDS in May 1994 .
Mary Leigh ( née Brown , 1885 - -1978 ) was an English political activist and suffragette .
Marie Perolz ( 7 May 1874 -- 12 December 1950 ) was also known as Mary Perolz and Máire Perolz , and as Miss Peroze in one crucial document .
Charles Burlingame Waite ( born in Wayne County , New York , 29 January 1824 ; died 1909 ) was a United States lawyer , jurist and author .
Simon - Pierre Denys de Bonaventure ( 22 June 1659 -- 7 February 1711 ) was an officer in the colonial troupes de la marine of New France and was heavily involved with the events of Acadia from 1685 until his death .
Moriz Benedikt ( sometimes spelled Moritz ) ( 27 May 1849 -- 18 March 1920 ) , a Viennese Jew born in Krasice , was a long - time editor of Neue Freie Presse and a powerful figure in Austrian politics and society .
John Isaac Hawkins ( 1772 - -1855 ) was an inventor who practised civil engineering .
William Sanford La Sor ( 1911 - -1991 ) was professor emeritus of Old Testament at Fuller Theological Seminary in Pasadena , California .
Henry of Ghent ( c. 1217 -- 29 June 1293 ) was a scholastic philosopher , known as Doctor Solemnis ( the Solemn Doctor ) , and also as Henricus de Gandavo and Henricus Gandavensis .
Thomas Johannes Lauritz Parr ( 13 May 1862 -- 12 August 1935 ) was a Norwegian educator and psychologist .
Chris Baldo ( real name Christian Baldauff , 24 June 1943 - 24 January 1995 ) was a Luxembourgish singer .
Rabbi Yosef Eliyahu Henkin ( 1881 - -1973 ) was a prominent Orthodox rabbi in the United States .
Bekri Mustafa Pasha ( known by the epithet Tekirdağlı , meaning `` from Tekirdağ '' ; died January 1690 ) was an Ottoman grand vizier during the Great Turkish War .
Sir Andrew Riccard ( c. 1604 -- 6 September 1672 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1654 .
Jens Christian Hauge ( 15 May 1915 -- 30 October 2006 ) , often written Jens Chr .
The Reverend John Galbraith Graham MBE ( 16 February 1921 -- 26 November 2013 ) was a British crossword compiler , best known as Araucaria of The Guardian .
Camilla Martelli ( c. 1545 -- 30 May 1590 ) was first the lover and then the second wife of the Grand Duke of Tuscany , Cosimo I de ' Medici .
Pierre Woeiriot de Bouzey ( 1532 - -1599 ) was a French engraver , goldsmith , painter , sculptor and medallist .
Friedrich Hustedt ( 1886 -- 1 April 1968 ) was a German teacher and botanist , best known for his diatom systematics research .
John Doull ( November 1 , 1878 -- 1969 ) was a lawyer , judge and politician .
Spyrydon Lytvynovych ( Ukrainian : Спиридон Литвинович , Polish : Spirydion Litwinowicz ; 6 December , 1810 -- 4 June , 1869 ) was the Metropolitan Archbishop of the Ukrainian Greek Catholic Church from 1864 until his death in 1869 .
Devendra Goel ( 3 March 1919 - 26 February 1979 ) was an Indian film director and producer of Bollywood films and best known for his work in the 1950s and early 1960s .
John S. Gibson , Jr. ( 1902 - -1987 ) was a powerful San Pedro , California , politician who was on the Los Angeles City Council for thirty years between 1951 and 1981 .
Richard Newport , 1st Baron Newport ( 7 May 1587 -- 8 February 1651 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1629 .
Henry Almond ( 1850 - -1910 ) helped form Stoke Ramblers ( now Stoke City ) in 1863 .
Filippo Coppola was an Italian composer , maestro di cappella of the Chapel Royal of Naples from 1658 to 1680 .
Charles A. Zimmermann ( 1861 -- 16 January 1916 ) was an American composer of marches and popular music .
Mary Thomas née Harris ( 30 August 1787 -- 10 February 1875 ) was a diarist , poet and early settler of South Australia .
Betty Bolton ( 7 January 1906 -- 2 April 2005 ) was a British actress , beginning as a child star during World War I and continuing her career in the 1920s and 1930s .
Zhang Gui ( Chinese : 張軌 , 255 - -314 ) was the governor of Liang province and first Duke of Xiping under Western Jin .
Edward John Cobbett ( 1815 - -1899 ) was an English watercolour and oil painter , a pupil of Joseph William Allen .
Giuseppe Aprile ( 28 October 1731 -- 11 January 1813 ) was an Italian castrato singer and music teacher .
Rosaura Andreu ( 1 January 1918 -- 21 November 2010 ) was a Cuban - born actress who found wide fame in Puerto Rico as a children 's television show host .
Andrew Dalgleish ( 1853 -- 1888 ) on Karakoram Pass , between Ladakh , India and China was a Scottish trader , traveller and government agent during the Great Game .
Dov Zakin ( Hebrew : דב זכין‎ , 1922 -- 4 September 1986 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment and Mapam between 1969 and 1977 and again from 1981 until 1984 .
Brigadier General James Roy Andersen ( 10 May 1904 -- 26 February 1945 ) was a United States Army Air Forces officer .
Seweryna Szmaglewska ( 1916 - -1992 ) was a Polish writer , known for both books for children and adults alike .
Jorge Alberto Garramuño ( 14 September 1953 -- 7 September 2015 ) was an Argentine politician who was a Senator for the Fueguino People 's Movement between 2013 and 2015 .
Richard Carmarden ( died 1603 ) was an English merchant , member of the Merchant Taylors Company , and Surveyor of the Customs for London .
Gerino da Pistoia , also Gerino di Antonio Gerini , ( 1480 - 1529 ) was an Italian painter and designer of the Renaissance .
Dušan Zbavitel ( 7 May 1925 -- 7 August 2012 ) was a world - renowned Czech Indologist .
Benjamin Ingham ( 11 June 1712 ( O.S. ) - 1772 ) , was born and raised in the Yorkshire and Humber region of England .
Maud de Lacy , Baroness Geneville ( 1230 -- 11 April 1304 ) was a Norman - Irish noblewoman and wealthy heiress who upon the death of her grandfather , Walter de Lacy , Lord of Trim and Ludlow inherited half his estates .
Giuseppe Salvatore Bellusci ( 31 May 1888 -- 26 December 1972 ) was an Italian politician of Arbëresh descent .
Jean Baptiste Édouard Verreaux ( 16 September 1810 -- 14 March 1868 ) was a French naturalist , collector and dealer .
Jorge R. Acosta ( 1904 - -5 March 1975 ) was a Mexican archaeologist who worked on numerous major archaeological sites in Mesoamerica , including Chichen Itza , Teotihuacán , Oaxaca , Palenque , Monte Albán and Tula .
George Tierney PC ( 20 March 1761 -- 25 January 1830 ) was an Anglo - Irish Whig politician .
Erik Sjöqvist ( 15 July 1903 -- 16 July 1975 ) was the director of Swedish Cyprus Expedition and director of Swedish Institute at Rome , Italy and professor of classical archaeology at Princeton University .
Cai Xiang ( Chinese : 蔡襄 ; pinyin : Cài Xiāng ; Wade -- Giles : Ts'ai Hsiang ) ( 1012 - -1067 ) was a Chinese calligrapher , scholar , official , structural engineer , and poet .
Dem I. Dobrescu ( usual rendition of Demetru Ion Dobrescu ; 1869 - -1948 ) was a Romanian left - wing politician who served as Mayor of Bucharest between February 1929 and January 1934 .
Sultan Ahmad Shah of Malacca ( died 1513 ) was a sultan of what is now Malaya .
Rose Hacker ( 3 March 1906 -- 4 February 2008 ) was a British socialist , writer , sex educator and campaigner for social justice .
Eli Uzan ( Hebrew : אלי אוזן‎ ) ( 21 March 1963 -- 23 November 2009 ) was an Israeli footballer who played for Hapoel Be'er Sheva , Hapoel Tel Aviv and Tzafririm Holon .
Sam Bernard ( 5 June 1863 - 16 May 1927 ) was an English stage , film and vaudeville star .
William Raymond Dommersen , also ( van ) Dommersheusen and ( van ) Dommersheuzen , ( London , Stratford West Ham , end 1859 -- London , 1927 ) was an English painter of Land- and Seascapes , Villages and Towns .
Sir Henry Gough , 1st Baronet ( 1709 -- 1774 ) , also known as Sir Harry , was a British politician .
Enrique Enríquez the Younger ( died 1366 ) was a nobleman of Castile , son of Enrique Enríquez the Elder .
Helen Crawfurd Anderson ( 9 November 1877 -- 18 April 1954 ) was a Scottish suffragette and Communist activist .
Louis Oppenheim ( 1879 - -1936 ) was a German graphic artist , painter and type designer .
Johan Vilhelm Gertner ( 10 March 1818 -- 28 March 1871 ) was a Danish painter , best known for his portraiture .
Manzo Iwata ( 9 February 1924 -- 4 June 1993 ) was a Japanese martial artist .
Constantin Marselis or Constantijn Marselis ( 28 November 1647 - 16 June 1699 ) was a nobleman of the wealthy Dutch Marselis family .
John Bancks ( 1709 -- 19 April 1751 ) , also known as John Banks , was an English writer .
Rudolf Bürger ( 31 October 1908 -- 20 January 1980 ) was a Romanian international footballer of German ethnicity in the 1920s and 1930s who is one of a few men who participated in each of the three pre - War FIFA World Cups .
Thanas Floqi ( 14.01.1884 - 1945 ) was an Albanian educator and patriot , and one of the signatories of the Albanian Declaration of Independence .
Stan Lawler ( 19 November 1909 -- 26 March 1958 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Abraham Rapoport ( Schrenzel ) was a Polish Talmudist ; born at Lemberg ( currently Lviv , Ukraine ) in 1584 ; died in 1651 ( June 7 ) ; son of Rabbi Israel Jehiel Rapoport of Cracow and son - in - law of R. Mordecai Schrenzel of Lemberg .
David Robert Wingate ( February 20 , 1819 -- 1899 ) was an American lumber businessman and plantation farmer who served in the Confederate Army as the commissioner of defense for Jefferson County , Texas , during the American Civil War .
Dr. John Oswald Sanders ( October 17 , 1902 - -October 24 , 1992 ) was a general director of Overseas Missionary Fellowship ( then known as China Inland Mission ) in the 1950s and 1960s .
Jacob Senleches ( fl . 1382/1383 -- 1395 ) ( also Jacob de Senlechos ( i.e. Senleches ) and Jacopinus Senlesses ) was a Franco - Flemish composer and harpist of the late Middle Ages .
Frank M. Casto ( 30 May 1875 -- 25 April 1965 ) was an American orthodontist who attended Angle School of Orthodontia in 1902 .
William Brodie Gurney ( 1777 - -1855 ) was a famed English shorthand writer and philanthropist of the 19th century .
Ezer Griffiths OBE , FRS ( 27 November 1888 -- 14 February 1962 ) was a Welsh physicist most noted for his work on the insulation properties of metals , heat transference , evaporation and refrigiration .
John MacDougall Hay ( 1879 - -1919 ) was a Scottish novelist , best known for his work Gillespie .
John Howard Van Amringe ( 1836 - -1915 ) was an educator and mathematician from the United States .
Tomislav Pinter ( 16 June 1926 -- 15 August 2008 ) was a Croatian cinematographer , regarded as the most significant cinematographer in Croatian cinema due to the artistic quality of his work and his prolific career spanning almost five decades .
Dr Shimon Kanovitch ( Hebrew : שמעון כנוביץ'‎ , born 6 July 1900 , died 25 July 1961 ) was an Israeli physician and politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Progressive Party and Liberal Party between 1959 and 1961 .
Tony Sheridan ( Anthony Esmond Sheridan McGinnity ; 21 May 1940 -- 16 February 2013 ) was an English rock and roll singer - songwriter and guitarist .
Henrietta Catherine Agnes of Anhalt - Dessau ( born 5 June 1744 in Dessau ; died : 15 December 1799 in Dessau ) was a princess of Anhalt - Dessau by birth , Dean of Herford Abbey and by marriage Baroness of Loën .
Arthur Bartholomew ( 3 December 1833 Bruton , Somerset -- 19 August 1909 Melbourne ) was an English - born Australian engraver , lithographer and natural history illustrator .
Leonardo de Figueroa ( c. 1650 , Utiel -- 1730 , Seville ) was a Spanish architect active in Seville .
Sir George Arthur Harwin Branson PC ( 11 July 1871 -- 23 April 1951 ) , known professionally as G. A. H. Branson , was an English barrister who became a judge of the High Court of Justice .
Lorna Wing , OBE , FRCPsych ( 7 October 1928 -- 6 June 2014 ) was an English psychiatrist and physician .
Willie Kemp , King of the Cornkisters ( born 1888 in Oldmeldrum -- 1965 ) is best known as a singer and writer of Doric comic songs .
Hector Alastair Hetherington ( 31 October 1919 -- 3 October 1999 ) was a British journalist , newspaper editor and academic .
Ippolito de ' Medici ( 1511 -- 10 August 1535 ) was the illegitimate only son of Giuliano di Lorenzo de ' Medici .
Ioan Hristea ( 17 March 1897 -- 1972 , Sibiu ) was a Romanian Officer during World War II .
Bahram Alivandi ( 1928 - 21 May 2012 ) was an Iranian - born Modern artist living in Vienna , Austria .
James Ross , 4th Lord Ross of Halkhead ( died 2 April 1581 ) was a Scottish nobleman and an adherent to the cause of Mary , Queen of Scots .
Thanassis Skordalos ( Greek : Θανάσης Σκορδαλός ; born 10 December 1920 -- 23 April 1998 ) was a musician from Crete , noted for playing the lyra , the bowed string instrument of Crete and most popular surviving form of the medieval Byzantine lyra .
Ishbel MacAskill ( née MacIver , 14 March 1941 -- 31 March 2011 ) was a heritage activist and traditional Scottish Gaelic singer and teacher , often referred to as the `` Gaelic diva '' .
Abu al - Khaṭṭāb ʻAbd al - Ḥamīd ibn ʻAbd al - Majīd ( Arabic : أبو الخطاب عبد الحميد بن عبد المجيد ; died 177 AH/793 CE‎ ) , commonly known as Al - Akhfash al - Akbar ( Arabic : الأخفش الأكبر‎ ) was a notable Arab grammarian .
Andreas Murray ( 9 August 1695 - 1771 ) was a German - born Swedish priest , founder of the Swedish Murray family .
Said Sheikh Samatar ( Somali : Saciid Sheekh Samatar , Arabic : سعيد الشيخ سمتر‎‎ ; 1943 - -24 February 2015 ) was a prominent Somali scholar and writer .
John O'Connor Power ( 13 February 1846 -- 21 February 1919 ) was an Irish Fenian and a Home Rule League and Irish Parliamentary Party politician and as MP in the House of Commons of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland represented Mayo from June 1874 to 1885 .
Ann Macbeth ( Bolton 1875 - -1948 ) was a British embroideress and author , a part of the Glasgow Movement and an associate of Charles Rennie Mackintosh .
Conrad Frederick Sauer ( October 13 , 1866 - 1927 ) was a German American pharmacist from Richmond Virginia who founded the C.F. Sauer Company on October 13 , 1887 , his 21st birthday .
Sir Henry Spurrier ( 16 June 1898 -- 17 June 1964 ) was a British engineer and industrialist , and the third generation of the Spurrier family to head Leyland Motors .
Richard Ernest Kunze ( b. in Altenburg , Germany , 7 April 1838 ; d. 1919 ) was a physician .
Julius Brammer ( 9 March 1877 -- 18 April 1943 ) was an Austrian librettist and lyricist .
Mr Tiz ( 2 February 1984 -- 30 January 2014 ) was a champion New Zealand thoroughbred racehorse .

Sigmund Hemmel ( 1520 - -1565 ) was a German composer , tenor , and Kapellmeister in Stuttgart , Württemberg .

Nicolas Martiau ( 1591 - -1657 ) was a Frenchman who immigrated to the English colony of Virginia in the 17th century .
Charles Andrew Dyce ( 1816 - -1853 ) was born in St Nicholas , Aberdeen , Scotland to parents William Dyce and Margaret Chalmers who were married on 8 Feb 1798 .

Robert Roper ( 1757 - -1838 ) was an English architect who practised from an office in Preston , Lancashire .

Harold Mathews Brett ( 1880 - -1955 ) was an American illustrator and painter best known for his New England scenes and portraits .

Speedball 2 Tournament is a sequel to the Commodore Amiga futuristic sports video game Speedball originally created by The Bitmap Brothers , published by Frogster Interactive Pictures and developed by Kylotonn .

Driveclub ( stylised as DRIVECLUB and sometimes stylised as # DRIVECLUB ) is a 2014 racing video game for the PlayStation 4 , developed by Evolution Studios and published by Sony Computer Entertainment .

The Hellion is a 1924 American Western film directed by Bruce M. Mitchell and featuring Boris Karloff .
The Lane That Had No Turning is a lost 1922 American silent film that was directed by Victor Fleming .

Diary of a Cannibal ( also known as Cannibal ) is a 2007 United States production horror film directed by Ulli Lommel .

Vaniusha and The Space Pirate ( Russian : Ванюша и космический пират ) is a 1991 Soviet Russian stop - motion animation film by Vladimir Danilevich .

Marked for Murder is a 1945 American film directed by Elmer Clifton .
The Raindrop ( Turkish : Güle Güle ) is a 2000 Turkish comedy - drama film , directed by Zeki Ökten , which chronciles the friendship of five elderly residents of Bozcaada .

Rathna Manjari ( Kannada : ರತ್ನ ಮಂಜರಿ ) is a 1962 Indian Kannada film , directed by Hunsur Krishnamurthy and produced by Hunsur Krishnamurthy and D Puttaswamy .
Show Biz Bugs is a 1957 Warner Bros. Looney Tunes animated short directed by Friz Freleng and featuring Mel Blanc as the voices of Bugs Bunny and Daffy Duck .
I.K.U. ( pronounced ai - kei - ju , abbreviated as iku ? ) is a 2001 independent film directed by Taiwanese - American experimental filmmaker Shu Lea Cheang .

Delhi in a Day is a 2011 Hindi independent film directed by Prashant Nair .
The Last Ones Shall Be First ( German : Die Letzten werden die Ersten sein ) is a 1957 West German crime film directed by Rolf Hansen , based on the short play The First and the Last by John Galsworthy .
Sith Apprentice is a Star Wars fan film that made its debut on the internet on March 29 , 2005 , directed by John E. Hudgens and co - written by Hudgens , Denny Humbard , and Men in Black creator Lowell Cunningham .
First Knight is a 1995 medieval film based on Arthurian legend , directed by Jerry Zucker .
The FP is a 2011 American comedy film written and directed by Brandon and Jason Trost .
Shikkar ( English : The Hunt , Malayalam : ശിക്കാര്‍ ) is a 2010 Malayalam mystery - thriller film directed by M. Padmakumar and written by S. Suresh Babu which was produced by Sreeraj Cinema .
White House Down is a 2013 American action thriller film directed by Roland Emmerich about an assault on the White House by a paramilitary group and the Capitol Police Officer who tries to stop them .
Bleak Night ( Hangul : 파수꾼 ; RR : Pasuggun ; lit . `` The Lookout '' ) is a 2010 South Korean coming - of - age drama film written and directed by Yoon Sung - hyun .
The Scarlet Pumpernickel is a animated Warner Bros. Looney Tunes theatrical cartoon short released in 1950 , directed by Chuck Jones and written by Michael Maltese .
The Employer is an award - winning psychological thriller written and directed by Frank Merle .
Battle for the City ( Finnish : Taistelu Turusta ) is a 2011 Finnish documentary film directed by Jouko Aaltonen about the city of Turku .

Fred L. Block is an American sociologist , and Professor of Sociology at the University of California , Davis .

Jordi Folch Pi ( March 25 , 1911 -- October 3 , 1979 ) was a Catalan biochemist at Harvard University ( McLean Hospital ) who is recognized universally as one of the founders of the field of structural chemistry of complex lipids and as a leader in the development of Neurochemistry as a distinct discipline within the Neurosciences .
Dr. Allan Abbass ( born February 22 , 1962 ) is professor , psychiatrist , and founding Director of the Centre for Emotions and Health at Dalhousie University in Halifax , Canada .

Miguel Zamacoïs , born in Louveciennes on September 8 , 1866 , and died in Paris on March 20 , 1955 , was a writer , poet and journalist , son of the Spanish Basque painter Eduardo Zamacois y Zabala and Marie Louise Perrin .

Cedric Price FRIBA ( 11 September 1934 -- 10 August 2003 ) was an English architect and influential teacher and writer on architecture .
Luigi Bartolini ( February 8 , 1892 -- May 16 , 1963 ) was an Italian painter , writer , and poet .
Ferdinand Rudio ( born August 2 , 1856 in Wiesbaden , died June 21 , 1929 in Zurich ) was a German and Swiss mathematician and historian of mathematics .

Henri - Paul Deyvaux - Gassier ( 1883 - -1951 ) was a French caricaturist and illustrator .

Piotr Michałowski ( July 2 , 1800 -- June 9 , 1855 ) was a Polish painter of the Romantic period , especially known for his many portraits , and oil studies of horses .
Paul - Émile Lecoq de Boisbaudran , also called François Lecoq de Boisbaudran ( 18 April 1838 -- 28 May 1912 ) , was a French chemist known for his discoveries of the chemical elements gallium , samarium and dysprosium .

After fighting on the Eastern Front , he accompanied the rescue mission that freed the deposed Italian dictator Benito Mussolini from captivity .

Denzil Holles , 1st Baron Holles PC ( 31 October 1599 -- 17 February 1680 ) was an English statesman and writer , best known as one of the Five Members whose attempted unconstitutional arrest by King Charles I in the House of Commons of England in 1642 sparked the Civil War .
Östen Dahl ( born 4 November 1945 in Stockholm ) is a Swedish linguist and professor best known for pioneering a marker - based approach to tense and aspect in linguistic typology .
Hristo Tatarchev ( Bulgarian : Христо Татарчев , Macedonian : Христо Татарчев , December 16 , 1869 - January 5 , 1952 ) was a Bulgarian revolutionary and first leader of the revolutionary movement in Macedonia and Eastern Thrace ( the organization was renamed to IMARO in 1906 and IMRO in 1920 ) .
László Kövér ( Kövér László , Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈkøveːr ˈlaːsloː ) , born on 29 December 1959 ) is a Hungarian politician and the current Speaker of the National Assembly of Hungary .
Daniel Múgica ( born 4 April 1967 , San Sebastián ) is a writer and film director , son of the Spanish politician Enrique Múgica Herzog and Faustina Díaz Azcona .
Gernot Böhme ( January 3 , 1937 , Dessau ) is a German philosopher and author , contributing to the philosophy of science , theory of time , aesthetics , ethics , and philosophical anthropology .
Bogdan Zakrzewski ( born 25 September 1916 in Poznań , died 23 October 2011 in Wrocław ) was a Polish historian and researcher of Polish literature .

The submarine was laid down on 7 July 1941 at the Nordseewerke yard at Emden as yard number 211 , launched on 30 June 1942 and commissioned on 25 August under the command of Kapitänleutnant Georg - Wilhelm Basse .

James M. Northup ( October 8 , 1820 -- October 20 , 1899 ) was an American farmer , merchant , banker and politician from New York .

Kinda Hibrawi ( Arabic : كندة هبراوي‎ ) ( born June 11 , 1978 ) is a Syrian American artist .
Vinal G. Good ( January 6 , 1906 - December 23 , 2000 ) was an American politician and lawyer from Maine .
Gordon Matta - Clark ( born Gordon Roberto Echaurren Matta ; June 22 , 1943 -- August 27 , 1978 ) was an American artist best known for his site - specific artworks he made in the 1970s .

Rock Allen ( born September 5 , 1981 in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania ) is a boxer in the Welterweight division .

William Bradley Kincaid ( July 13 , 1895 -- September 23 , 1989 ) was an American folk singer and radio entertainer .
Ashley Turner is an American singer - songwriter , pianist , and vocal coach .
Phillip Nixon ( also known as Philip Nixon or Phil Nixon ) is a British composer and graphic designer for video games .
Hugo Falcandus was a historian who chronicled the reign of William I of Sicily and the minority of his son William II in a highly critical work entitled The History of the Tyrants of Sicily ( or Liber de Regno Sicilie ) .
Pablo Salazar Mendiguchía ( born in Soyaló , Chiapas , on August 9 , 1954 ) is a Mexican politician and ex - governor .
Arwut Chinnapasaen ( Thai : อาวุธ ชินนภาแสน ; born December 3 , 1980 ) is a Thai former swimmer , who specialized in sprint freestyle events .

Hellmut Lantschner ( November 11 , 1909 -- July 4 , 1993 ) was an Austrian and German alpine skier and world champion .

Edward Salisbury Dana ( November 16 , 1849 -- June 16 , 1935 ) was an American mineralogist and physicist .
John R. Buckley ( born January 1 , 1932 in Rockland , Massachusetts ) is an American politician who served as Massachusetts Secretary of Administration and Finance from 1975 to 1979 , member of the Massachusetts House of Representatives from 1965 to 1975 , and Abington , Massachusetts Town Treasurer from 1961 to 1965 .

Lenny Von Dohlen ( born December 22 , 1958 ) is an American film , television and stage actor , known for his performance as architect Miles Harding in the film Electric Dreams and as the orchid - growing agoraphobic Harold Smith in the television series Twin Peaks .

Jose De Jesus ( born August 8 , 1968 in Cayey , Puerto Rico ) is a retired professional boxer in the light flyweight ( 108 lb ) division .
Rupert Nigel Pendrill Hadow known as Pen Hadow ( born 26 February 1962 ) , is founding director of Geo Mission Ltd , an environmental sponsorship organisation , and British polar guide and explorer .

Robert Bice ( March 14 , 1914 -- January 8 , 1968 ) , was an American television and film actor .
Joseph Jastrow ( January 30 , 1863 -- January 8 , 1944 ) was a Polish - born American psychologist , noted for inventions in experimental psychology , design of experiments , and psychophysics .
Lev Navrozov ( Russian : Лев Наврозов ; born 1928 in Moscow ) is a Russian author , historian and polemicist and father of poet Andrei Navrozov .
Gina Catalino ( born in 1984 ) is a New Hampshire native singer - songwriter best known for her song , 11:32 PM .
Baldassare Calamai ( Florence , November 13 , 1797 - July 11 , 1851 ) was an Italian painter , active in a neoclassical style , painting mainly historical subjects .
Mohammad Shadab Kabir Siddiqi ( born November 12 , 1977 , Karachi , Sindh ) is a Pakistani cricketer who played in 5 Tests and 3 ODIs from 1996 to 2002 .
Damodran Nair is a former Fijian politician of Indian descent , who held the Tavua Open Constituency in the House of Representatives for the Fiji Labour Party ( FLP ) in a by election on 17 January 2004 following the death of the incumbent , Pravin Singh , in an automobile accident in late 2003 .
Galen Hadley ( born March 9 , 1942 , in Lincoln , Nebraska ) is an American politician who is a member the Nebraska Legislature , serving as Speaker of the Nebraska Legislature since January 2015 .
Aaron Feldman is an American professional photographer , best known as the founder and CEO of True Photography Weddings , the largest wedding photo business in San Diego , California .
Irvin Alberti is an actor and humourist from the Dominican Republic .

Died October 12 , 1902 , in Nigeria ) was an early explorer of Africa , Agent General of the British Government who signed treaties with many African chiefs which allowed the British to establish the Southern Nigeria Protectorate .

Don Matteo is an Italian television series that has been airing since 2000 on the premier channel of Italian national television , Rai 1 .
Time Team Digs is a British television series that aired on Channel 4 in 2002 .
Mulligrubs was an Australian television series that aired on Network Ten from 3 October 1988 to 27 December 1996 .
Inside Politics is a television current news program on CNN .
Bad Robots is a British television prank show on E4 .
Ego Trip 's Miss Rap Supreme is an American reality television series that airs on the VH1 cable network .
The Nine Lives of Chloe King is an American fantasy drama television series which premiered on ABC Family on June 14 , 2011 , and ended on August 16 , 2011 .
Hulk Hogan 's Rock ' n ' Wrestling is an American animated television series that originally aired on CBS Saturday mornings from September 14 , 1985 to December 6 , 1986 , with reruns airing until June 27 , 1987 .
10vor10 ( literally `` 9.50 pm '' ) is the title of a current affairs show on German - speaking Swiss public television channel SRF 1 .
My Gym Partner 's a Monkey is an American animated television series that was created by Tim Cahill and Julie McNally - Cahill and produced by Cartoon Network Studios .
To Nisi ( Greek : Το Νησί ; English : The Island ) is a Greek television series based on the best - selling English novel The Island by Victoria Hislop airing on Mega Channel .
T - Bag is a witch - like character who appears in a television series that ran from 1985 to 1992 on Children 's ITV .
The Mysti Show was a British children 's television programme , produced by Mystical Productions for the BBC in 2004 - 2005 .
Flop Show is an Indian television sitcom that first aired on Doordarshan in 1989 .
24 Hours in the Past was a BBC One living history TV series first broadcast in 2015 .
See It Now was an American newsmagazine and documentary series broadcast by CBS from 1951 to 1958 .
Pair of Kings is an American television sitcom shown on the cable channel Disney XD .
Big Love is an American television drama that aired on HBO between March 2006 and March 2011 .
South of Sunset is an American TV detective series , starring musician / actor Glenn Frey , that only aired one episode on CBS in 1993 .
Dash Dolls is an American reality television series that premiered on the E ! cable network , on September 20 , 2015 .
Football Huddle was a Canadian sports talk show television series which aired on CBC Television in 1960 .
Kurt Vonnegut 's Monkey House is a Canadian television anthology series which aired on the Showtime network from 1991 to 1993 .
¡ Qué buena se puso Lola ! , it is a Venezuelan telenovela produced and broadcast by RCTV .
Gemini Man is an American action / adventure drama series that aired on NBC in 1976 .
The Paul Winchell Show , or The Paul Winchell and Jerry Mahoney Show , or The Spiedel Show , was a variety program which aired on NBC prime time from 1950 to 1954 , starring ventriloquist Paul Winchell and his dummy , Jerry Mahoney .
Kareena Kareena was a Zee TV comedy serial that aired from September 1 , 2004 to 17 October 2005 .
True Crime with Aphrodite Jones is an American documentary television series airing on Investigation Discovery , hosted by Aphrodite Jones .
Face the Nation is an American Sunday morning political interview show broadcast on the CBS television network .
Tough Cookies is a comedy television series that aired on CBS in 1986 ; six episodes were broadcast .
Special Unit 2 is an American sci - fi / comedy television series , filmed in Vancouver , BC that aired on UPN for two seasons from April 2001 through February 2002 .
New Zealand 's Top 100 History Makers was a weekly television programme first shown on Prime Television New Zealand on 6 October 2005 .

Grill Me is a USA Network game show that aired its pilot ( and only episode ) on September 9 , 1996 .
Buku Harian Nayla ( Nayla 's Diary ) is an Indonesian Christian television drama which aired on RCTI .
The Chevrolet Tele - Theatre is an American anthology series that aired live on NBC Mondays at 8 pm EST from September 27 , 1948 to June 26 , 1950 .
Broken News is a comedy programme shown on BBC Two in late 2005 .
Dhani Tackles the Globe was an American documentary television series hosted by NFL linebacker Dhani Jones of the Cincinnati Bengals , currently airing on the Travel Channel ; the series followed Jones around the globe as he learned how to play international sports and simultaneously explored the culture of each location .
The Voice of Vietnam ( Vietnamese : Giọng hát Việt ) is a reality television singing competition created by John de Mol . It is scheduled to premiere in Vietnam in July 2012 on Vietnam Television .
Next Caller is an unaired American television comedy series that was scheduled to premiere mid - season on NBC as part of the 2012 - -13 television schedule .
The Arena Football League on ESPN is a presentation of the league with games airing on ESPN , ESPN2 , ESPNEWS , and ESPN3 as with all other sports the ESPN family of networks all Arena Football games air on The WatchESPN App also .
Naked Josh was a Canadian television series broadcast on Showcase .
69 Sexy Things 2 Do Before You Die ( stylized 69 Sexy Things 2 Do B4U Die ) was a Playboy TV adult newsmagazine profiling exotic locales , outdoor adventures and current erotic trends .
Carinurella paradoxa is a species of crustacean in family Niphargidae , and the only species in the genus Carinurella .
Drynaria , commonly known as basket ferns , is a genus of ferns in the family Polypodiaceae .
Hypolaena is a plant genus in the family Restionaceae , described as a genus in 1810 .
The Malagasy crowned eagle ( Stephanoaetus mahery ) , also known as the Madagascar crowned hawk - eagle , was a large bird of prey , comparable in size to the African crowned eagle , that inhabited Madagascar until 1500 AD .
The Balsas shiner ( Notropis boucardi ) is a species of freshwater fish endemic to Mexico .
Streptostyla is a genus of predatory , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Spiraxidae .
Physocarpus , commonly called ninebark , is a genus of flowering plants in the family Rosaceae , native to North America ( most species ) and northeastern Asia ( one species ) .
The Electra 's tree - nymph ( Idea electra ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The African gecko , Cnemaspis africana , is a species of gecko found in Central Africa .

The Hispaniolan edible rat ( Brotomys voratus ) is an extinct species of rodent in the family Echimyidae .
Alnus viridis ( green alder ) is an alder distributed widely across the cooler parts of the Northern Hemisphere .

The Chelidae are one of three living families of the turtle suborder Pleurodira and are commonly called the Austro - South American side - neck turtles .
The Swinhoe 's rail ( Coturnicops exquisitus ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
The Bhutan giant flying squirrel ( Petaurista nobilis ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Macrocheraia is a genus of bug in the family Largidae with a single species , Macrocheraia grandis found mainly in Southeast Asia but extending into parts of South Asia .
Furconthophagus is a genus of Scarabaeidae or scarab beetles in the superfamily Scarabaeoidea , more usually treated as a subgenus of Onthophagus
Bryopsidales is an order of green algae , in the class Bryopsidophyceae .
Purshia ( bitterbrush or cliff - rose ) is a small genus of 5 - 8 species of flowering plants in the family Rosaceae , native to western North America , where they grow in dry climates from southeast British Columbia in Canada south throughout the western United States to northern Mexico .
Osyris is a genus of plants in the family Santalaceae , one of the many genera known as sandalwoods .
Orchipedidae is a flatworm family in the sub order Echinostomata .
The D'Entrecasteaux Archipelago pogonomys ( Pogonomys fergussoniensis ) , also known as the D'Entrecasteaux Archipelago tree mouse , is a species of prehensile - tailed rat from the family Muridae that is endemic to Papua New Guinea .
The Rio skate ( Rioraja agassizii ) is a shallow water skate native to the Atlantic coast of South America from Brazil to southern Argentina .
Phanagnathus overlaeti is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Phanagnathus .
Paxia is a genus of plants in the family Connaraceae , first described as a genus in 1891 .
Clingfishes are fishes of the family Gobiesocidae , belonging to the order Gobiesociformes .
Ventridens is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Zonitidae , the true glass snails .
Brachyctis rugulosa is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Brachyctis .
Paracerceis is a genus of isopod crustacean in the family Sphaeromatidae .
Manatees ( family Trichechidae , genus Trichechus ) are large , fully aquatic , mostly herbivorous marine mammals sometimes known as sea cows .
Dipelta is a genus of three large , deciduous shrubs that are members of the family Caprifoliaceae .
Auximobasis is a genus of the gelechioid moth family Blastobasidae .
The Atlantic thread herring , Opisthonema oglinum , is a herring - like fish in the family Clupeidae .
Lagden 's bushshrike ( Malaconotus lagdeni ) is a bird species in the bushshrike family ( Malaconotidae ) .
Condalia is a genus of spiny shrubs in the tribe Rhamneae of the buckthorn family , Rhamnaceae .
Acamptopappus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Asteraceae described as a genus in 1873 .
Nolana is the only genus in the Solanaceae which has a fruit composed of mericarps , although its flower and other vegetative morphology is similar to other plants in this family .
Ussuritidae are ancestral , Triassic , Phylloceratina characterized by generally smooth , discoidal , evolute shells with rounded venters and little or no ornamentation and by sutures with primitive monophyllitic saddles with a single terminal branch or leaflet .
Trematotegmen is an extinct genus of trematosaurian temnospondyl within the family Trematosauridae .

Ablattaria is a genus of burying beetles or carrion beetles belonging to the family Silphidae .
Xenoceltitidae are evolute , generally ribbed , upper Lower Triassic Ceratitida with ceratitic or goniatitic sutures ; formerly included in the Noritaceae but now placed in the Xenodiscaceae .
Eurymerus eburioides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Eurymerus .
Reineckeiidae is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod famuly belonging to the superfamily Perisphinctoidea .
The Christmas frigatebird or Christmas Island frigatebird ( Fregata andrewsi ) is a seabird of the frigatebird family Fregatidae which is endemic to Christmas Island in the Indian Ocean .

Lambdotheriidae is an extinct family of the Perissodactyla ( odd - toed ungulate ) order ( that is , browsing and grazing animals ) .
The Milagros ' tiger ( Parantica milagros ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .

The European pied flycatcher ( Ficedula hypoleuca ) is a small passerine bird in the Old World flycatcher family .

Jardinella is a genus of small freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Kittlidiscidae is an extinct family of Middle Triassic gastropods in the superfamily Pleurotomarioidea , named to contain the genus Kittlidiscus and included in the Vetigastropoda .

Pantadenia is a genus of plants under the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1925 .

Paratya is a genus of freshwater shrimp of the family Atyidae , found in various islands in the Pacific Ocean .
Pelicans are a genus of large water birds that makes up the family Pelecanidae .
Cimicoidea is the name of a superfamily of insects belonging to the infraorder Cimicomorpha that have a mandible modified as a straw - like rostrum used for feeding on animals as their host or prey .
The Indian pipistrelle ( Pipistrellus coromandra ) is a species of bat in the family Vespertilionidae found in Afghanistan , Bangladesh , Bhutan , Cambodia , India , Myanmar , Nepal , Pakistan , Sri Lanka , Thailand , and Vietnam .

The Bearded puffer , Sphoeroides tyleri , is a species in the family Tetraodontidae ( or pufferfish ) which is typically found in marine coastal waters of the West Atlantic from Colombia to Southeastern Brazil .
The Port Jackson shark ( Heterodontus portusjacksoni ) is a nocturnal , oviparous ( egg laying ) type of bullhead shark of the family Heterodontidae , found in the coastal region of southern Australia , including the waters off Port Jackson .

The Cravenoceratidae is one of six families included in the ammonoid superfamily Neoglyphiocerataceae , which lived during the latter part of the Paleozoic era .

The Hispaniolan yellow - mottled frog or painted robber frog , Eleutherodactylus pictissimus , is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to Hispaniola and found in both the Dominican Republic and Haiti .

The Guabang Shan salamander , Hynobius guabangshanensis , is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to China , as it is only known from the locality from where it was described as a new species to science in 2004 , at Guabang Shan Tree Farm in Qiyang County of Hunan Province .
The Costa Rican brush finch or grey - striped brush finch ( Arremon costaricensis ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .

The Worcester 's buttonquail or Luzon buttonquail ( Turnix worcesteri ) -- named after Dean Conant Worcester -- is a species of bird in the Turnicidae family .
Strepsirrhini or Strepsirhini ( i/ˌstrɛpsəˈraɪniː/ ; STREP - sə - RY - nee ) is a suborder of primates that includes the lemuriform primates , which consist of the lemurs of Madagascar , galagos ( `` bushbabies '' ) and pottos from Africa , and the lorises from India and southeast Asia .
Eureptilia ( `` true reptiles '' ) is one of the two major clades of the Sauropsida , the other being Anapsida ( or Parareptilia ) .

Platycleis is a genus of insect described by Fieber in 1852 , belonging to the family Tettigoniidae , subfamily Tettigoniinae .
Salim Ali 's fruit bat ( Latidens salimalii ) is a rare megabat species in the monotypic genus Latidens .
