Alsophylax is a genus of small species of geckos , endemic to Central Asia , commonly known as straight - fingered geckos .
Schayera is a grasshopper genus in the family Acrididae .
Slender stone loach ( Balitora mysorensis ) is a species of hill - stream loach .
Blennius is a Genus of Perciform fish in the family Blenniidae .
Pentabrachion is a plant genus from the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1864 .
Commelinoideae is a subfamily of monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family ( Commelinaceae ) .
The Zoopagales is an order of fungi in the subphylum Zoopagomycotina .
Leptogorgia is a genus of soft coral in the family Gorgoniidae .
It contains a single named species , Osteodontornis orri ( Orr 's Bony - toothed Bird , in literal translation of its scientific name ) , which was described quite exactly one century after the first species of the Pelagornithidae ( Pelagornis miocaenus ) was .
The Asian glossy starling ( Aplonis panayensis ) is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
The Olympic marmot ( Marmota olympus ) is a rodent in the squirrel family Sciuridae ; it occurs only in the U.S. state of Washington , on the middle elevations of the Olympic Peninsula .
Hondalagus represents the smallest and most specialized member of the extinct family Argyrolagidae .
The Yucatan squirrel ( Sciurus yucatanensis ) is a tree squirrel in the genus Sciurus endemic to Belize , Guatemala , and Southeast Mexico .
The Mount Gargues pipistrelle ( Pipistrellus aero ) is a species of vesper bat found in Kenya and possibly Ethiopia .
Entelurus aequoreus , the Snake pipefish , is a species of pipefish native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean where they are generally found amongst algae close in to shore .
The Amapa tree frog , Hypsiboas dentei , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in northern Brazil in the Amapá state ( where its type locality , Serra do Navio , is located ) , French Guiana , and southeastern Suriname .
The Treur River barb ( Barbus treurensis ) or simply Treur barb is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Staga is a monotypic genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , containing the single species Staga producta from Madagascar .
The Patzcuaro frog ( Rana dunni ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family endemic to the Michoacán state , Mexico , where it is locally known as rana de Pátzcuaro .
The Hawequa flat gecko ( Afroedura hawequensis ) is a species of lizard in the family Gekkonidae .
Ede Vadászi ( September 13 , 1923 in Budapest -- June 12 , 1995 in Budapest ) , aka Ede Viboch , was a Hungarian basketball player who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Elisabetta Preziosa ( born 21 September 1993 ) is an Italian artistic gymnast She represented her country at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Alfred Viggo Emil Andreasen ( later Fjordvald ; September 4 , 1895 -- May 26 , 1972 ) was a Danish boxer who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Khashbaataryn Tsagaanbaatar ( Mongolian : Хашбаатарын Цагаанбаатар ) is the single medal winner from Mongolia at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Marcel Lalu ( 24 March 1882 -- 1951 ) was a French gymnast who competed in the 1900 Summer Olympics , in the 1908 Summer Olympics , and in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Johan Petter Åhlén ( 13 April 1879 -- 31 March 1939 ) was a Swedish curler who won a silver medal at the 1924 Winter Olympics .
Fritz Kopperschmidt ( born 22 December 1939 in Hamburg ) is a German former sailor who competed in the 1964 Summer Olympics and in the 1968 Summer Olympics .
Eduardo Barragán ( born July 1 , 1951 in Cartagena de Chairá , Bolívar ) is a retired Colombian boxer , who competed for his South American nation at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich , West Germany .
Shawn Estrada ( born April 1 , 1985 in East Los Angeles , California ) is an undefeated Mexican American professional boxer in the Super Middleweight division and was a U.S. Olympian at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Witold Woyda ( May 10 , 1939 -- May 5 , 2008 ) was a Polish fencer who won four Olympic medals in the foil between 1964 and 1972 , including two gold medals at the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Fiona Butler ( born 16 October 1977 ) is a South African former field hockey player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics and in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
After the World War II Laila Schou Nilsen competed in alpine skiing at the 1948 Winter Olympics in St. Moritz , where she finished 7th in downhill and 14th in slalom .
Rudolf Körner ( born January 8 , 1892 in Leipzig / Germany , date of death 13 . November 1978 in Füssen / Germany ) was a German gymnast who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Juan Mata missed all of Chelsea 's pre - season games as he was playing for Spain at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London , but he returned to play in the 2012 FA Community Shield against Manchester City and was substituted after 74 minutes for Daniel Sturridge .
Nilton Pacheco de Oliveira ( July 26 , 1920 -- June 26 , 2013 ) was a Brazilian basketball player who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics in London , United Kingdom .
Klapa s Mora is a music ensemble that represented Croatia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2013 in Malmö with the song `` Mižerja '' .
Karlo Umek ( 8 February 1917 -- 25 September 2010 ) was a Slovenian Olympic shooter who participated for Yugoslavia at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome in the Men 's Free Pistol , 50 metres event , where he placed 22nd .
Sir Geoffrey Cornewall , 6th Baronet ( 7 May 1869 -- 21 January 1951 ) of Moccas Court , Herefordshire , was a British archer who competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics in London .
Luis Usoz ( 19 October 1932 in San Sebastián -- 10 March 1992 ) was a Spanish field hockey player who competed in the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Nikolai Vekšin ( 23 May ( O.S. 10 May ) 1887 in Haapsalu , Governorate of Estonia , Russian Empire -- 15 January 1951 in Norillag , Norilsk , Russian SFSR , Soviet Union ) was an Estonian sailor who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics .
Dennis van der Geest ( born June 27 , 1975 ) is a Dutch judoka , who won the bronze medal in the men 's heavyweight ( + 100 kg ) division at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Rolf Tschiemer ( born October 23 , 1951 ) is a retired Swiss professional ice hockey forward who played for SCL Tigers in the National League A. He also represented the Swiss national team at the 1976 Winter Olympics .
William Hehir ( born 21 January 1887 , date of death unknown ) was a British track and field athlete who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics in racewalking events .
Kamil Djamaloudinov ( born August 15 , 1979 in Dagestan ) is a boxer from Russia , who won the bronze medal in the featherweight division ( -- 57 kg ) at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney , Australia .
Sven Goldemann ( born 22 June 1969 ) is the lead for the German curling team that competed in Curling at the 2014 Winter Olympics --
Olivier Bausset ( born February 1 , 1982 ) is a French sailor and Olympic athlete who won a bronze medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
At the 1976 Winter Olympics in Innsbruck , Piet Kleine became Olympic Champion on the 10,000 m , beating world record holder Sten Stensen -- who won silver -- in a close race .
Ileana Ongar ( born 24 March 1950 in Alexandria ) is a former Italian hurdler , that was 8th at 1976 Summer Olympics ( 110 m hs ) and earned four medals at the Mediterranean Games .
Reza Naderian ( Persian : رضا نادریان‎ , born January 29 , 1989 in Isfahan , Iran ) is an Iranian Taekwondo athlete who competed in the Men 's 58 kg at the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Scott Vitale ( born 6 July 1985 ) was a member of the Australian wheelchair rugby team which competed in the 2004 and 2008 Summer Paralympics .
Rik Van Linden ( born 28 July 1949 in Wilrijk , Antwerp ) is a Belgian former road bicycle racer who won the points classification in the 1975 Tour de France .
Abdellah Bidane ( born 19 August 1967 ) , also known as Abdellah Bidar , is a Moroccan football defender who played for Morocco in the 1986 FIFA World Cup .
Georgia Coleman ( January 23 , 1912 -- September 14 , 1940 ) was an American diver who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics and in the 1932 Summer Olympics .
Carlos Ventosa Delmas ( born April 3 , 1971 ) is a former backstroke swimmer from Spain , who competed at the 1992 Summer Olympics for his native country .
Soul Militia ( known until 2002 as 2XL ) is an Estonian hip - hop act , internationally most notable for winning the Eurovision Song Contest 2001 as backing singers for Tanel Padar and Dave Benton , with the song `` Everybody '' .
Eric Shirley ( born 3 April 1929 ) ran the 3,000 metres steeplechase final at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne , Australia for Great Britain with team mates Chris Brasher and John Disley ; coming in 8th with a time of 8.57 .
József Munk ( born November 11 , 1890 -- died ? ) was a Hungarian freestyle swimmer who competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics .
Maxim Aleshin is a Russian acrobat and former gymnast who won a Bronze Medal at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney .
Heli Rantanen ( born 26 February 1970 in Lammi ) is a Finnish javelin thrower , who won the gold medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , United States .
Kieran Hansen ( born 16 November 1971 in Sydney ) is an Australian short track speed skater who competed in the 1992 Winter Olympics , in the 1994 Winter Olympics , and in the 1998 Winter Olympics .
Attila Laták ( 9 September 1945 -- 8 December 1991 ) was a Hungarian wrestler who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Domingo González ( 24 December 1947 -- 16 July 1979 ) was a Colombian footballer who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Ines Geißler ( born 16 February 1963 in Marienberg , Saxony ) , commonly spelled Ines Geissler in English , is a former butterfly swimmer from East Germany , who won the gold medal in the 200 m butterfly at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow , Soviet Union .
Ebrahim Javadi ( Persian : ابراهیم جوادی‎‎ , born July 28 , 1943 in Qazvin ) is an Iranian wrestler who competed in Freestyle at the 1972 Summer Olympics .

Charles - Étienne Jordan ( Berlin , 1700 - 1745 ) was a Prussian - born Huguenot refugee , advisor to Frederick the Great and French - language author on literature and history .
Jeanne Thérèse du Han de Martigny ( 30 October 1707 in Lunéville -- 7 May 1748 in Nancy ) was born and baptized the same day in Lunéville , in the duchy of Lorraine , now part of France .

Hermann Hirt ( 19 December 1865 in Magdeburg -- 12 September 1936 in Gießen ) was German philologist and Indo - Europeanist .

Karl Gerhardt ( born Boston , Massachusetts , 7 January 1853 ; died Shreveport , Louisiana 7 May 1940 ) was a United States sculptor .
Dr François Carlo Antommarchi ( born 5 July 1780 in Morsiglia , Corsica -- d. 1838 in Santiago de Cuba , Cuba ) was Napoleon 's physician from 1818 to his death in 1821 .

Christa Reinig ( 6 August 1926 , Berlin -- 30 September 2008 , Munich ) was a German poet , fiction and non - fiction writer , and dramatist .

Macrosiphini is a bug tribe in the subfamily Aphidinae .
Argyrodes chionus is a species of tangle - web spider that is endemic to Aldabra in the Seychelles .
Lythraria salicariae is a species of Chrysomelidae family , that is common in Palaearctic Region east to Korea .
The Palaeodictyopteroidea or Paleodictyopterida are an extinct superorder of Palaeozoic beaked insects , characterised by unique mouthparts consisting of 5 stylets .
Larinia elegans is an orb - weaving spider species found from Austria to China .
Atta vollenweideri , common name chaco leafcutter ant , is a species of leaf - cutter ant , a New World ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae of the genus Atta .
Plesitomoxia atra is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the genus Plesitomoxia .
Rohdea is a genus of native to eastern Asia ( China , Japan , the Himalayas and Indochina ) .
Tetradymia stenolepis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Mojave cottonthorn .
Rhenanorallus is a genus of prehistoric rail which existed in Mainz Basin , Germany during the late Oligocene or early Miocene .
Cylindropuntia californica is a species of cactus known by the common names California cholla , snake cholla , and cane cholla .
Masdevallia nidifica is a species of orchid found from Central America into northern Peru .
Barcinosuchus ( meaning `` Cerro Barcino Formation 's crocodile '' ) is an extinct genus of carnivorous metasuchian from the early Cretaceous period .
Erigeron lemmonii is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Lemmon 's fleabane .
The Aracanidae are a family of bony fishes related to the boxfishes .
Mikadocephalus is an extinct genus of ichthyosaur .
Brickellia betonicifolia ( betonyleaf brickellbush ) is a Mexican species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
The Personidae are a family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Meconella is a small genus of flowering plants in the poppy family .
Melastoma is a genus in the family Melastomataceae .
Polystachya subdiphylla is a species of orchid native to Tanzania , in the Nguru Mountains and Uluguru Mountains .
Sarcocystis nesbitti is a species of protozoon .
Carabus hummeli vladobydovi is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Russia , where it can only be found in Maritime Province .
Eriastrum abramsii is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Abrams ' woollystar .
Callicarpa dichotoma ( common names , Purple Beautyberry or Early Amethyst ) is species of beautyberry .
Triacanthus biaculeatus , also known as the Short - nosed tripod fish , is a species of marine fish in the family Triacanthidae .
Cathariostachys madagascariensis , the Madagascar giant bamboo or Volohosy in Malagasy language , is a bamboo species found in Madagascar .
Astragalus anisus is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Gunnison milkvetch .
The Pebas stubfoot toad ( Atelopus spumarius ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
The family Ripiphoridae ( formerly spelled Rhipiphoridae ) is a cosmopolitan group of beetles , commonly known as wedge - shaped beetles , containing some 450 species .
Cyprina ligeriensis is an extinct species of saltwater clam , a fossil marine bivalve mollusk in the family Arcticidae .
The Zammarini is a tribe of cicadas .
Bolodon is a genus of extinct mammal from the Lower Cretaceous of Europe , and possibly the Upper Jurassic of North America .
It contains only one species , Ratasa alienalis , which is found in Russia .
Gagea trinervia is a Mediterranean species of small bulbous perennial plants lily family .
Melica schuetzeana is species of grass in the Poaceae family that is found in Bhutan and in the Chinese provinces Qinghai , Sichuan and Yunnan .
Gilia tenuiflora is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name greater yellowthroat gilia .
Lobelia deckenii ( syn . Lobelia keniensis ) is a species of giant lobelia of the mountains of East Africa .
Eulimnadia texana , the Texas clam shrimp or desert shrimp , is a species of crustacean in the family Limnadiidae .
Barisia is a genus of lizards in the family Anguidae .
Dromaeosauridae is a family of feathered theropod dinosaurs .
Bellastraea aurea , common name the golden small star , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Agonum variolatum is a species of beetle from Carabidae family that is endemic to the US state of California .
Rheum undulatum is a plant species in the genus Rheum found in Asia .
Valenzuela gynapterus is a species of Psocoptera from Caeciliusidae family that can be found in Finland , France , Germany , Latvia , Luxembourg , Norway , Poland , Romania , Spain , Sweden , Switzerland , and the Netherlands .
Antillesoma is a genus of peanut worms ( Phylum Sipuncula ) .
Diplodonta globus is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Ungulinidae .
Suillellus adonis is a species of bolete fungus found in Croatia .
Callipogon is a genus of beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae .
The Tatama Climbing Salamander ( Bolitoglossa tatamae ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
The Alvord cutthroat trout , Oncorhynchus clarki alvordensis , was a subspecies of cutthroat trout .
Melicope makahae , Makaha Valley melicope , is a species of plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae .
Paramphilius baudoni is a species of loach catfish found in Cameroon , the Republic of Congo and Gabon .
Bayerotrochus tangaroanus , common name : the Tangaroan Slit Shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
Ilypnus is a genus of gobies native to the eastern Pacific Ocean coasts of California , USA to Baja California , Mexico .
Ammonoceratites is an extinct genus of ammonoid cephalopod known from the Albian ( upper Lower Cretaceous ) of British Columbia , Madagascar , New Zealand , and Japan , included in the Lytoceratidae .
Protremaster is an extinct genus of sea star that lived in the Early Jurassic(Age range : 196.5 to 189.6 Ma ) .
Pseudoparmena borchmanni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudoparmena .
Araucaria columnaris , the Coral reef araucaria , Cook pine , New Caledonia pine , Cook araucaria , or columnar araucaria , is a unique species of conifer in the Araucariaceae family .
Ilex gardneriana was a species of plant in the Aquifoliaceae family .
Asclepias L. ( 1753 ) , the milkweeds , is an American genus of herbaceous perennial , dicotyledonous plants that contains over 140 known species .
The red bull ant ( Myrmecia gulosa ) , also known as the giant bull ant or `` hoppy joe '' , is a species of bulldog ant from the genus Myrmecia .
Acacia meiantha is a species of flowering plant in the Fabaceae family .
Hoya kerrii is a species of Hoya native to the south - east of Asia .
Rutilus meidingerii is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family found in Austria , Germany , and Slovakia .
Ischnacanthus is an extinct genus of fish in the class Acanthodii .
Amphicyclotulus dominicensis is a species of tropical land snail with a gill and an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Neocyclotidae .
Clematis napaulensis is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family , Ranunculaceae , native to China and the Indian subcontinent .
Shorea palosapis ( also called Philippine Mahogany or White Lauan ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Oedaleops is an extinct genus of caseasaur synapsid from the Early Permian of the southwestern United States .
The Cucarrón or Cucharón ( Gyranthera darienensis ) is a species of flowering plant in the Malvaceae sensu lato or Bombacaceae family .
Leccinum holopus , commonly known as the white birch bolete , white bog bolete , or ghost bolete , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae found in northern Asia , Europe , and northeastern North America .
Kinkonychelys ( `` Lac Kinkony Study Area turtle '' ) is an extinct genus of side - necked turtle which existed in Madagascar during the Late Cretaceous period .
It contains only one species , Patagobia thursbyi , which is found in Chile and Argentina where it is known from temperate montane woodlands and grasslands in Patagonia .
Historis is a genus of butterflies in the Nymphalidae family found from Mexico to South America .
Allium altaicum is a species of onion native to Asiatic Russia ( Altay , Buryatiya , Zabaykalsky Krai , Irkutsk , Tuva , Amur Oblast ) , Mongolia , Kazakhstan and northern China ( Inner Mongolia , Heilongjiang and Xinjiang ) .
Mazocraeidae is a flatworms family in the order Mazocraeidea .
†Onychochilidae is an extinct family of small , fossil , upper Cambrian to lower Devonian molluscs .
Aeschronectida is an extinct order of mantis shrimp - like crustaceans which lived in the Mississippian subperiod in what is now Montana .
Cocytius is a genus of hawkmoths .
Centrolene lynchi , sometimes known as the Lynch 's giant glass frog , is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Alcyonidium diaphanum or the `` Sea - chervil '' is a species of bryozoan found in the North Atlantic .
Cerastium glomeratum is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names sticky mouse - ear chickweed and clammy chickweed .
Rhinotyphlops is a genus of blind snakes found in Africa , the Middle East and India .
Ribes hirtellum is a North American species of gooseberry known by the common names American gooseberry , hairy - stem gooseberry , hairy gooseberry , and wedge - leaf gooseberry , native to Canada and to the northeastern and north - central United States .
Parischnogaster jacobsoni is a species of social wasp within Parischnogaster , the largest and least known genus of Stenogastrinae .
Balsamorhiza macrolepis is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower tribe of the aster family , known by the common name California balsamroot .
Aethriamanta circumsignata known as the square - spot basker is a species of dragonfly in the Libellulidae family .
Archaeosporales is an order of fungi that may form arbuscular mycorrhiza or endocytosymbioses with cyanobacteria .
Haloquadratum walsbyi is a species of archaea discovered in a brine pool in the Sinai peninsula of Egypt .
Rhopalogaster is a genus of hypogeous Basidiomycetes .
Amynothrips andersoni is a species of thrips known as alligator weed thrips .
Brodavis is a genus of freshwater hesperornithiform birds known from the Late Cretaceous ( possibly Campanian and Maastrichtian stage ) of North America and Asia .
Lilaeopsis genus of several species of flowering plants in the family Apiaceae . Known commonly as grassworts .
Girella cyanea , the blue drummer , is a species of sea chub native to inshore waters , around 6 metres ( 20 ft ) depth , from Australia to New Zealand and the Kermadec Islands .
Minolia subangulata , common name the subangular margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Solariellidae .
Rhadinosuchus is an extinct genus of proterochampsian archosauriform reptile from the Late Triassic .
Tegula gallina ( or commonly , Speckled Tegula ) is a North American species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae .
Presbyornis is an extinct genus of anseriform bird .
Napecoetes is a genus of moths in the family Psychidae .
Bagrichthys obscurus is a species of bagrid catfish which is found in Cambodia , Laos , Thailand and Vietnam where it is found in the Chao Phraya , Bang Pakong and Mekong drainages .
Hoplostethus vniro is a small deep - sea fish species belonging to the slimehead family ( Trachichthyidae ) .
Sticta venosa is a species of lichen in the family Lobariaceae .
Metacmaeops vittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Metacmaeops .
Neotomoxia castaneroides is a species of beetle in the Neotomoxia genus that is in the Mordellidae family , which is a part of the Tenebrionoidea superfamily .
Psammobatis is a genus of fish in the Rajidae family .
Mimulus tilingii is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Tiling 's monkeyflower .
Xylia xylocarpa is a species of tree in the Mimosoideae subfamily of the Fabaceae family .
Eunephrops is a genus of lobsters , containing four species , all found in the Western Atlantic Ocean :
Penstemon personatus is an uncommon species of penstemon known by the common name closethroat beardtongue .
Geastrum jurei is a species of fungus in the Geastrales , or earthstar fungi .
Ariomma is a genus of deepwater , marine perciform fishes .
Austroplatypus incompertus is a species of ambrosia beetle belonging to the weevil family , native to Australia , with a verified distribution in New South Wales and Victoria .
Quercus oocarpa is a Mesoamerican species of oak in the beech family .
Helicina orbiculata , also known as Helicina ( Oligyra ) orbiculata and as Oligyra orbiculata , is a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Helicinidae .
Teratohyla is a small genus of glassfrogs in subfamily Centroleninae .
Inanidrilus is a genus of marine Annelid worms .
Nepenthes tomoriana ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz təmɒriˈɑːnə/ ; after Tomori Bay , from which the type originates ) is a species of pitcher plant endemic to Sulawesi , where it grows at an elevation of 0 - -500 m above sea level .
Ficus lacunata is a species of plant in the family Moraceae which is endemic to Ecuador .
Ostrya knowltonii is a species of tree known by the common names Knowlton 's hophornbeam , western hophornbeam , woolly hophornbeam , and wolf hophornbeam .
The only known species is Zygochloa paradoxa , commonly known as sandhill canegrass .
Haplochromis greenwoodi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria where they are found in the southeastern portion of the lake .
Disa purpurascens is a species of orchid found in South Africa ( SW . Cape Prov . ) .
Urophora mauritanica is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Urophora of the family Tephritidae .
The Philippine coucal ( Centropus viridis ) is a species of cuckoo in the Cuculidae family .
Species The only known species in the genus is Shinnersia rivularis , the Rio Grande bugheal or Mexican oak leaf plant , native to Texas , Coahuila , and Nuevo León .
Galinsoga mollis is a rare Mexican species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Patinopecten yessoensis ( Yesso scallop , Giant Ezo scallop , Ezo giant scallop ) is a species of scallop .
It contains the single species Santschiella kohli , described by Forel in 1916 from the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Estonioceras is an extinct genus of tarphyceridan nautiloid from the Ordovician of Europe .
Allium pendulinum , called Italian garlic , is a plant species known only from Sardinia , Sicily , Corsica and mainland Italy .
Senecio antisanae is a species of Senecio in the Asteraceae family found only in the subtropical or tropical moist montane region of Ecuador .
Zodarion remotum is a spider species found in Corsica and Italy .
Uropappus , commonly called silverpuffs , is a genus of North American plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
The West African lion ( Panthera leo senegalensis ) , also known as the Senegal lion , is a lion subspecies native to western Africa .
Gigantosaurus ( from the Greek `` Γίγας '' and `` σαυρος '' , meaning `` giant lizard '' ) is a sauropod dinosaur genus from the Late Jurassic Kimmeridge Clay Formation of England .
The species Paranauchenia denticulata lived in the Miocene epoch in Argentina .
Lactarius vietus ( commonly known as the grey milkcap ) is a species of fungus in the family Russulaceae , first described by Elias Magnus Fries .
It contains only one species , Dejoannisia pallidella , which is found in Mozambique .
Homotrysis is a genus of darkling beetle , described by Francis Polkinghorne Pascoe in 1866 .
Hypancistrus inspector is a species of armored catfish endemic to Venezuela where it occurs in the upper Negro , Casiquiare and upper Orinoco River basins .
Teocchiana pallida is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Teocchiana .
The Chamula mountain brook frog , Duellmanohyla chamulae , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Mexico .
Epapterus blohmi is a species of driftwood catfish distributed in the Orinoco River basin and Tuy River of the Caribbean coast of Venezuela .
Omomyidae is a family of early primates that radiated during the Eocene epoch between about 55 to 34 million years ago ( mya ) .
Artipe is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) of this genus are found in the Indomalaya ecozone , the Palearctic ecozone ( Himalayas - China ) and the Australasian ecozone ( New Guinea ) .
Lactobacillus parakefiri is a species in the genus Lactobacillus first isolated from kefir grains , hence its name .
Lybia australiensis is a species of small crab in the family Xanthidae .
Sinowilsonia is a monotypic genus of plant containing the single species Sinowilsonia henryi .
Arctostaphylos tomentosa is a species of manzanita known by the common name woollyleaf manzanita or woolley manzanita .
Hesperocolletes douglasi , the Rottnest bee , is an extinct species described from a single specimen collected in 1938 .
Epimecis hortaria , the tulip - tree beauty , is a species of Ennominae found in North America .
Ophrys tenthredinifera , the sawfly orchid , is a terrestrial species of orchid native to the Mediterranean region from Portugal and Morocco to Turkey .
Ictalurus lupus ( the bagre lobo or headwater catfish ) is a species of catfish in the family Ictaluridae .
Paravitrea clappi is a species of land snail in the family Zonitidae , the true glass snails .
Penstemon degeneri is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Degener 's beardtongue .
The restless demon , ( Indothemis limbata ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Priocnemis coriacea is a large species of pepsid spider wasp characterised by having plentiful erect hair on the face and propodum .
The Andropogoneae , sometimes called the sorghum tribe , are a large tribe of grasses ( family Poaceae ) with roughly 1,200 species in 90 genera , mainly distributed in tropical and subtropical areas .
Mammillaria carmenae ( Isla Carmen pincushion cactus ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cactaceae .
Salvia indica is a species of herbaceous perennial plant belonging to the family Lamiaceae .
Gundlachia triantha , the TransPecos goldenshrub or Trans - Pecos desert goldenrod , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
In 2008 , the genus Sophronitis was merged into Cattleya , making such nothogenera as Potinara , Sophrolaeliocattleya and Sophrocattleya no longer current , but only of historical interest .
Saniwa is an extinct genus of monitor lizards that lived during the Eocene epoch around 48 million years ago .
Emblemariopsis ramirezi is a species of chaenopsid blenny known from Venezuela , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
Plagiopyla is a genus of ciliate .
Venerupis philippinarum is an edible species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Veneridae , the Venus clams .
Conus omaria , common name the Omaria cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The Long - nosed bandicoots ( genus Perameles ) are members of the order Peramelemorphia .
Camassia cusickii , common name Cussick 's camas , is a species of plant in the Asparagaceae family ( subfamily Agavoideae ) .
Polystachya farinosa is a species of flowering plant in the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Cassida is a large genus of tortoise beetles in the subfamily Hispinae .
Phoenicopteridae is a wading bird family including flamingos and their close extinct relatives .
Clematis coactilis , common name Virginia white - hair leather flower , is a plant species endemic to the western part of the US State of Virginia .
Aspidoceras is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod genus that lived during the Late Jurassic ( Kimmeridgian ) with a fairly broad distribution .
Haemogregarina is a genus of haemoprotozoans , parasitic mainly on cold - blooded vertebrates .
Senecio mohavensis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Mojave ragwort .
Gutierrezia wrightii is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Wright 's snakeweed .
Crossosoma bigelovii , known by the common name ragged rockflower , is one of only a few species in the flowering plant family Crossosomataceae .
The genus Systropha comprises several species of Old World sweat bees , primarily specialist pollinators of plants in the genus Convolvulus .
Jianchangopterus is a genus of scaphognathine rhamphorhynchid pterosaur from the Middle Jurassic of western Liaoning , China .
Dolichuranus is an extinct genus of dicynodont therapsid from the Middle Triassic of Africa .
Cylindrosybra albomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cylindrosybra .
Azibiidae is an extinct family of fossil primate from the late early or early middle Eocene from the Glib Zegdou Formation in the Gour Lazib area of Algeria .
Assiminea gittenbergeri is a species of minute operculate snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Assimineidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Trichodothella blumeri .
Pilophorus perplexus is a species of bug in the Miridae family that can be found everywhere in Europe ( except for Azores , Canary Islands , Cyprus , Iceland , Island , and Novaya Zemlya ) .
Allium tripterum is a plant species endemic to a small region near Mingora , in northwestern Pakistan .
Cartieraspis is an extinct genus of placoderm fish , which lived during the Middle Devonian period in North America .
Quasicyclotosaurus is an extinct genus of mastodonsauroid temnospondyl of the Moenkopi Formation .
Heterostropha was a previously used taxonomic category , an order of sea snails , within the superorder Heterobranchia .
Veronicella cubensis , common name the Cuban slug , is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Veronicellidae , the leatherleaf slugs .
Schiedea spergulina is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name canyon schiedea and spreading schiedea .
Pseudograpsus setosus ( Spanish : jaiba peluda ) is a species of edible crab endemic to the coasts of Chile , Ecuador and Peru ; it is a benthic predator that lives in the subtidal and intertidal zones in temperate waters from sea levels down to depths of 45 metres ( 150 ft ) .
The Gonorynchiformes are an order of ray - finned fish that includes the important food source , the milkfish ( Chanos chanos , family Chanidae ) , and a number of lesser - known types , both marine and freshwater .
Syncrossus hymenophysa ( commonly known as tiger loach , tiger botia or green tiger loach ) is a species of freshwater fish in the loach family Botiidae .
Erythronium umbilicatum ( Dimpled trout lily ) is a species of flowering plant in the lily family .
Koiloskiosaurus is an extinct genus of procolophonid parareptile from the Early Triassic of Germany .
Huntleya citrina is a species of orchid that occurs in western Colombia and Ecuador .
Himantoglossum adriaticum , the Adriatic lizard orchid , is a species of orchid native to Italy , Croatia , Austria , and the Czech Republic .
Bryopsidophyceae is a class of chlorophyte green algae .
Mastodonsaurus ( meaning `` breast tooth lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Middle Triassic .
Dendropemon is a genus of mistletoes which is endemic to the Caribbean .
Antodynerus is an afrotropical and indomalayan genus of potter wasps .
Orthochilus ensatus is a species of orchid , occurring from Mozambique to South Africa .
Resnova humifusa is a bulbous perennial plant species in the genus Resnova found in South Africa .
The Biak scrubfowl or Biak megapode ( Megapodius geelvinkianus ) is a species of bird in the Megapodiidae family .
Ziziphus nummularia , also called Jharber ( Hindi : झड बेर ) , is a species of Ziziphus native to the Thar Desert of western India and southeastern Pakistan and south Iran ( where it is called رمیلک ramilak in Persian ) .
Hassar orestis is a species of thorny catfish that is native to the countries of Brazil , Colombia , Ecuador , Guyana , Peru and Venezuela .
Allium borszczowii is a plant species native to Uzbekistan , Kazakhstan , Turkmenistan , Iran , Afghanistan and Pakistan .
Sphaeromeria simplex is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Laramie chickensage and Laramie false sagebrush .
Digitalis ( /ˌdɪdʒᵻˈteɪlᵻs/ or /ˌdɪdʒᵻˈtælᵻs/ ) is a genus of about 20 species of herbaceous perennials , shrubs , and biennials commonly called foxgloves .
Neoferdina is a genus of starfish in the family Goniasteridae .
The Bulgariaceae are a family of fungi in the order Helotiales .
Cichla orinocensis , sometimes known as the Orinoco peacock bass ( `` peacock bass '' is also used for some of its relatives ) , is a very large species of cichlid .
Agropyron is a genus of Eurasian plants in the grass family ) , native to Europe and Asia but widely naturalized in North America .
Eucalyptus langleyi , commonly known as Green Mallee Ash , Nowra Mallee , Nowra Mallee Ash or Albatross Mallee is an endangered Eucalyptus species native to south - eastern New South Wales , Australia .
Streptanthella is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the mustard family containing the single species Streptanthella longirostris , which is known by the common name longbeak streptanthella , or simply streptanthella .
Deraeocoris schach is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Deraeocorinae .
Bothriochloa saccharoides is a species of grass known by the common name silver bluestem .
Archaeoattacus edwardsii , common name Edward 's Atlas Moth , is a species of moths belonging to the Saturniidae family , Saturniinae subfamily .
Rubus geoides is a South American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Sesleria heufleriana is a species of perennial grass in the Poaceae family , native to central , southeastern , and eastern Europe and the Caucasus .
Henosepilachna vigintisexpunctata , common name twentysix - spotted potato ladybird is a ladybird species .
Oncidium incurvum is a species of orchid endemic to Mexico ( Veracruz to Chiapas ) .
Noteridae is a family of water beetles closely related to the Dytiscidae , and formerly classified with them .
The Percophidae , duckbills , are a family of perciform fishes found in tropical and subtropical waters of the Atlantic and Indian Oceans and in the southwestern and southeastern Pacific .
Delphinium cardinale is a species of larkspur known by the common names scarlet larkspur and cardinal larkspur .
Nursallia is an extinct genus of pycnodontid ray - finned fishes , ranging from the Late Cretaceous period until its extinction during the Eocene ( from 99.7 to 94.3 Ma ) .
Blechnum colensoi , also known as Colenso 's hard fern , waterfall fern or peretao is a species of fern native to New Zealand .
Cystidicoloides tenuissima is a species of nematode in the order Spirurida .
Dundocharax bidentatus is a species of distichodontid fish endemic to Angola , where it is found in the Lucoge River .
Metallosticha plumbeifasciella is a species of snout moth in the genus Metallosticha .
Sideroxylon alachuense , known by the common names Alachua bully , silver bully and silvery buckthorn , is a plant species native to the US States of Georgia and Florida .
Aloe tenuior is an extremely variable species .
Seddera spinosa is a species of plant in the Convolvulaceae family .
Conus stercusmuscarum , common name the fly - specked cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
The genus Hydrochoerus contains two living species of capybaras from South America and Panama , the largest living rodents in the world .
Jacquemontia reclinata is a rare species of flowering plant in the morning glory family known by the common names beach clustervine , reclined clustervine , and beach jacquemontia .
Icarosaurus ( meaning `` Icarus lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of kuehneosaurid reptile from the Late Triassic ( Carnian age ) Lower Lockatong Formation of New Jersey , dated to around 228 million years ago .
Bagarius rutilus is a species of sisorid catfish native to Laos , Vietnam and Yunnan in China where it is found in the Nam Sam , Nam Ma and Red River basins .
Vesperus conicicollis is a species of brown coloured beetle in the Vesperidae family that can be found in Portugal , Spain , and on the island of Sardinia .
Eocyclotosaurus is an extinct genus of mastodonsauroid temnospondyl from the Middle Triassic ( Anisian ) .
Cassiope lycopodioides , Haida Gwaii mountain - heather or clubmoss mountain heather , is a plant species native to southern Alaska , British Columbia , and the US State of Washington .
Melica hunzikeri is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to southern South America .
Limnonectes liui is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Pseudergolis is a butterfly genus from the family Nymphalidae found in Southeast Asia .
Heliamphora glabra ( Latin : glaber = bald ) is a species of marsh pitcher plant native to Serra do Sol in Venezuela .
Neoiphinoe arctica is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Capulidae , the cap snails .
Vernonia is a genus of about 1000 species of forbs and shrubs in the family Asteraceae .
Aplestosuchus is an extinct genus of baurusuchid mesoeucrocodylian known from the Late Cretaceous Adamantina Formation of São Paulo , southern Brazil .
Pogonia japonica is a species of orchid occurring in East Asia .
Angulus emarginatus is a species of Angulus bivalve , mainly distbed in tidal zone of Mainland China .
Seitaad is a genus of sauropodomorph dinosaur which lived during the lower Jurassic period in what is now southern Utah , USA .
Hiatellidae is a taxonomic family of small saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs .
Scelidomachus socotranus is a species of spider found on the island of Socotra in the Indian Ocean .
Lithophaga bisulcata , or the mahogany date mussel , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Mytilidae .
Dodecatheon hendersonii is a species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae , native to western North America , from California north to southern British Columbia and Idaho .
Ochlerotatus is a genus of mosquito .
Delarbrea balansae is a species of flowering plant of family Myodocarpaceae endemic to New Caledonia .
Zamioculcas ( Common name `` Zanzibar Gem '' ) is a genus of flowering plant in the family Araceae , containing the single species Zamioculcas zamiifolia .
Ichnotropis is a genus of African lizards in the family Lacertidae .
Dorsanum miran , common name : the Moroccan bullia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Agnoderus gnomoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Agnoderus .
The Mascarene owls were those belonging to the genus Mascarenotus .
Western bean cutworm ( Striacosta albicosta ) is a species of moth of the Noctuidae family and the only member of the Striacosta genus .
Pectinodon is a genus of dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous period ( 66 mya ) .
Russula brevipes is a species of mushroom commonly known as the short - stemmed russula or the stubby brittlegill .
Notocheirus hubbsi is a species of surf sardine found along the Pacific coast of Argentina and Chile .
Brachinus psophia is a species of ground beetle from the Brachininae subfamily that can be found in Bulgaria , Greece , Italy , Albania , Austria , Czech Republic , France , Hungary , Moldova , Slovakia , Ukraine , all states of former Yugoslavia ( except for Macedonia ) , and in Western Europe .
Paracorynactis hoplites , usually known as the hoplites corallimorph , is a species of corallimorph from the western Indo - West Pacific .
Euptelea is a genus of two species of flowering plants in the monogeneric family Eupteleaceae .
Sufflogobius bibarbatus , the Bearded Goby or Pelagic Goby , is a species of goby native to the southeastern Atlantic Ocean .
Athylia viduata is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily .
Protospinax is an extinct genus of cartilaginous fish found in the Solnhofen limestones of southern Bavaria .
Pseudovertagus aluco , common name Aluco Vertagus or Cuming 's Cerith , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cerithiidae , the ceriths .
Bursa verrucosa is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Bursidae , known as the frog shells .
Quirimbaua castroi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Quirimbaua .
Montiaceae are a family of flowering plants , comprising about 14 genera with some 500 species , ranging from herbaceous plants to shrubs .
Lapampasaurus is an extinct genus of hadrosaurid iguanodont known from the Late Cretaceous Allen Formation ( late Campanian or early Maastrichtian stage ) of La Pampa Province , Argentina .
Apatosuchus is an extinct genus of non - crocodylomorph loricatan pseudosuchian known from the Late Triassic of Germany .
Afrolimnophila joana is a species of Limoniid crane fly in the family Limoniidae .
Blepisanis basirufipennis is a beetle species from the Cerambycidae family .
Carabus lefebvrei is a species of bluish - black coloured ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily , that is endemic to Sicily .
Coccinella novemnotata , the nine - spotted ladybug or nine - spotted lady beetle , is a species of ladybug native to North America .
Leucoagaricus leucothites , white dapperling , or white Agaricus mushroom , is a species of agaric fungus .
Tilia nasczokinii is considered a threatened species and included in the Red Book of Krasnoyarsk Krai .
Vombisidris is a genus of subarboreal and arboreal ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Eupatorus is a genus of rhinoceros beetles .
Raja rhina , also known as the longnose skate , is a species of skate mostly found on the Alaska Coastline , Eastern Bering Sea , Baja California , and the Gulf of California .
Asterias forbesi , commonly known as Forbes sea star , is a species of starfish in the family Asteriidae .
Saribus is a genus of palms ( family Arecaceae ) , native to Southeast Asia and Papuasia .
Lophocalotes is a genus of agamid lizard , containing a single species , Lophocalotes ludekingi , endemic to Sumatra , Indonesia , commonly called the crested lizard .
Rhipidomys is a genus of rodents in the family Cricetidae , comprising at least 18 species of climbing mouse :
Diplotaxodon is a small genus of seven formally described , as well as a number of undescribed , deep - water species of cichlid fish endemic to Lake Malawi in east Africa .
Symmorium is an extinct genus of stethacanthid shark .
Tellimya ferruginosa is a species of small marine bivalve mollusc in the family Montacutidae .
Grylloblatta campodeiformis , also known as the Northern Rock Crawler , is an omnivorous species of insect in family Grylloblattidae .
The parrot family Psittaculidae consists of five subfamilies , the Platycercinae , Psittacellinae , Loriinae , Agapornithinae and Psittaculinae .
Buccinum baeri , common name Baer 's Buccinum , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Phacochoerus is a genus of wild pigs in the family Suidae , known as warthogs .
Chlorophorus is a genus of round - necked longhorns belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Cerambycinae .
Gethyllis ( probably from Greek `` gethyon '' , bulb ) , commonly called Kukumakranka , Koekemakranka , or Kroekemakrank , is a genus of bulbous plant in the Amaryllis family .
Hedera algeriensis ( Algerian ivy ; syn . Hedera canariensis var . algeriensis Willd ) is a species of evergreen ivy native to the North African coast , including coastal mountains in Algeria .
Cooper 's mountain squirrel ( Paraxerus cooperi ) is a species of rodents in the family Sciuridae found in Cameroon and Nigeria .
Ophiogobius is a genus of gobies native to the coastal Pacific and Atlantic waters of southern South America .
Triops longicaudatus is one of the oldest animal species still in existence .
Strobilomyces foveatus is a little - known species of fungus in the Boletaceae family .
Funastrum clausum , commonly known as white twinevine , is a species of flowering plant in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae .
Tetradymia comosa is a species of flowering plant in the aster family , known by the common name hairy horsebrush .
Garrya flavescens is a species of flowering shrub , known by the common name ashy silktassel .
The genus it is considered monotypic , with the single species Nemaxera betulinella placed here .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Erikssonopsis ericae .
Bifidunguiglenea gestroi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Bifidunguiglenea .
Saltanecydalopsis irwini is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Saltanecydalopsis .
Cinnamodendron cubense is a species of flowering plant in the family Canellaceae .
Cyathula is a genus of medicinal and ornamental plants in the family Amaranthaceae .
Herpetotherium is an extinct genus of metatherian mammal .
Pyrgomantis simillima is a species of praying mantis found in Tanzania , Transvaal , and Zimbabwe .
Angiostrongylus vasorum , also known as French heartworm , is a species of parasitic nematode in the family Metastrongylidae .
Rhynchactis macrothrix is a species of whipnose angler found in the Atlantic and western Indian Oceans where it is found at depths of around 2,000 metres ( 6,600 ft ) .
Copadichromis ilesi is a species of fish in the Cichlidae family , which is endemic to Lake Malawi .
Agathotoma aculea is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mangeliidae
Mantoida is a genus containing eleven species of mantis .
Asterohyptis is a genus of the Lamiaceae , or mint family , first described in 1932 .
The Madagascan snipe has never been recorded elsewhere , and no other snipe species have yet been recorded on Madagascar .
Syneta betulae is a species of beetle from the family of leaf beetles , subfamily Synetinae .
Hokkaidornis is an extinct genus of penguin - like plotopterid from the Late Oligocene of Hokkaido , Japan .
Austroliotia densilineata , common name the close - lined austroliotia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Androsace is a genus in the family Primulaceae , second only to Primula in number of species .
Thonningia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Balanophoraceae containing the single species Thonningia sanguinea .
Lapsias lorax is a species of lapsiine jumping spider from Ecuador .
Poromya granulata , or the granular poromya , is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Poromyidae .
Oxycera pygmaea , the pygmy soldier , is a European species of soldier fly .
Plesiadapiformes ( `` Adapid - like '' or `` near Adapiformes '' ) is an extinct ( and possibly paraphyletic or polyphyletic ) order of mammals .
Pityopsis graminifolia is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name narrowleaf silkgrass .
Asterolasia asteriscophora , commonly known as lemon starbush , is a shrub species in the family Rutaceae .
Cypraecassis testiculus , common name the reticulated cowry helmet , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cassidae , the helmet snails and bonnet snails .
Inula is a large genus of about 90 species of flowering plants in the family Asteraceae , native to Europe , Asia and Africa .
Cymbella elegans is a diatom species in the genus Cymbella .
Coralliogalathea humilis is a species of squat lobster in a monotypic genus in the family Galatheidae .
Plectronoceras is the type genus of the family Plectronoceratidae .
Watsonisuchus is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Early Triassic of Australia , Madagascar , and South Africa .
Cleomella longipes , the Chiricahua Mountain stinkweed , is a plant species native to northern Mexico and to the southwestern United States .
Inia is a genus of river dolphins from South America .
Belidae is a family of weevils , called belids or primitive weevils because they have straight antennae , unlike the `` true weevils '' or Curculionidae which have elbowed antennae .
Trisetaria is a genus of plants in the grass family , native to Asia and to the Mediterranean region .
Gammarus baysali is a cave - dwelling species of freshwater amphipod crustacean , found in Turkey .
The Marsh Skimmer , also known as Tricolored Marsh Hawk , and Slender Blue Skimmer , ( Orthetrum luzonicum ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Parachondrostoma miegii is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Spain .
Cattleya elongata , the Cattleya with the Elongated Stalk , is an orchid species in the genus Cattleya endemic to the campo rupestre vegetation in northeastern Brazil .
Gibberula burnupi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cystiscidae , the margin snails .
Aptinoma is a small genus arboreal of ants in the subfamily Dolichoderinae .
Nemotelus pantherinus , the fen snout , is a European species of soldier fly .
Caralophia loxochila , the Slantlip eel , is a species of eel in the family Ophichthidae .
Neusticurus is a genus of gymnophthalmid lizards endemic to northern South America .
The Andean siskin ( Spinus spinescens ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Atractosteus is a genus of gars in the family Lepisosteidae , with three species .
Zabrus aetolus is a species of ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that is endemic to Greece .
Pthirus gorillae or gorilla louse is a species of parasitic sucking louse that afflicts gorillas .
Uroplatus sikorae is a species of gecko commonly referred to as the mossy leaf - tailed gecko .
Zodarion germanicum is a spider species of the Zodariidae family .
Myrmeleon pictifrons is a species of insect known commonly as ant - lion or doodlebug .
The Dendryphantinae are a subfamily of jumping spiders that occur mainly in the New World .
Glyphipterigidae is a family of small moths commonly known as sedge moths as the larvae of many species feed on sedges and rushes .
Pilularia minuta , is a species of fern belonging to the family Marsileaceae .
Ilex cookii ( Cook 's Holly or te ) is a species of plant in the Aquifoliaceae family .
The Acleistoceratidae , named by Flower in Flower & Kümmel 1950 , is a family of oncocerids that contains genera characterized by depressed ( or rarely compressed ) exogastric brevicones and cyrtocones ( Sweet , 1964 K398 ) that range from the Middle Silurian to the Middle Devonian .
Salix japonica is a species of willow native to hills and mountains of central Honshū ( Japan ) .
Gigantochloa is a tropical Asian and Papuasian genus of giant clumping bamboos in the grass family .
Polymita picta , common name the Cuban land snail or the Painted snail , is a species of large , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
Gonidiomyces is a fungal genus in the division Ascomycota .
Oliva mantichora , common name the amethyst olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
Eburia brunneicomis is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found in Belize , Guatemala and Mexico .
The Drakensberg minnow ( Labeobarbus aspius ) is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Congo Democratic Republic .
Adenanthos labillardierei is a species of erect shrub endemic to the slopes of the Barren Ranges in the Fitzgerald River National Park in southwest Western Australia .
Musa sikkimensis , also called Darjeeling Banana is a species of the genus Musa .
Angaria sphaerula is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc of the family Angariidae .
Sinibrama macrops is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sinibrama .
Stellepipona is a small ( 7 species currently recognized ) afrotropical genus of potter wasps .
Euclea balfourii is a species of plant in the Ebenaceae family .
Msuata is a genus of flowering plants in the ironweed tribe within the sunflower family .
Erigeron compactus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names cushion daisy , fernleaf fleabane , and compact daisy .
The spider genus Paratheridula with its single species P. perniciosa is widely distributed ; it is suspected that it is introduced .
Schisandra ( magnolia vine ) is a genus of twining shrub that generally climb on other vegetation .
Spiniphryne gladisfenae , the Prickly dreamer , is a species of dreamer known only from the Atlantic Ocean .
Lycaenidae is the second - largest family of butterflies ( behind Nymphalidae , brush - footed butterflies ) , with over 5,000 species worldwide , whose members are also called gossamer - winged butterflies .
The Orthoptera order of insects includes the grasshoppers , crickets , cave crickets , Jerusalem crickets , katydids , weta , lubber , Acrida , and locusts .
Amelanchier spicata , also referred to as the low juneberry , thicket shadbush , dwarf serviceberry , or low serviceberry ( historically also called `` pigeon berry '' ) , is a species of serviceberry that has edible fruit , which are really pomes .
Amtocephale ( meaning `` Amtgai head '' ) is a genus of pachycephalosaurid dinosaur from early Late Cretaceous ( Turonian - Santonian stages ) deposits of southern Gobi Desert , Mongolia .
Baryphracta is an extinct genus of diplocynodontinecrocodilian .
Rhacophorus owstoni is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to Japan .
It is placed in its own genus , Charruodon .
Elachorbis tatei is a species of minute sea snail with an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tornidae .
Penstemon haydenii , the blowout beardtongue or blowout penstemon , is a species of beardtongue in the Plantaginaceae family .
Belodontichthys is a genus of sheatfishes native to Asia .
Heterocondylus is a genus of Latin American flowering plants in the sunflower family .
It contains only one known species , Cyanixia socotrana , a perennial , herbaceous and bulbous plant species endemic to the Island of Socotra in the Indian Ocean , part of the Republic of Yemen .
Pelargorhynchus ( meaning `` stork beak '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish .
The Pimoidae spider family is a rather small group of 37 species in four genera .
Lupinus brevicaulis is a species of lupine known by the common names shortstem lupine and sand lupine .
Buriadia is a genus that existed from the Carboniferous to the Permian .
Vanilla bahiana is a species of vanilla orchid that is endemic to Bahia , located in eastern Brazil .
Euglandina texasianais a species of large predatory air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Spiraxidae .
Myochamidae is a family of saltwater clams , marine bivalves in the order Anomalodesmata .
Streptomyces hundungensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from a quarry in Tangkhul Hundung in Manipur in India Streptomyces hundungensis has antifungal activity .
Euvrilletta serricornis is a species of beetles in the genus Euvrilletta of the family Anobiidae .
Helianthus anomalus , Western sunflower , is a species of plants in the sunflower family , found in the southwestern United States .
Hiboka is a spider genus in the family Idiopidae with only one species , Hiboka geayi , found in Madagascar .
Blasisaurus is a genus of lambeosaurine hadrosaurid dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous .
Carex ericetorum , known as rare spring sedge , is a perennial species of plants in the sedge family Cyperaceae native to central Europe and western Asia growing on calcareous soils in short grassland .
Brachionichthys was , until recently , the only genus in the family Brachionichthyidae ( commonly known as handfishes ) , but presently five genera are placed in this family of anglerfishes .
Zeatrophon pulcherrimus is a species of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
Ranunculus cymbalaria is a species of buttercup known by the common names alkali buttercup and seaside buttercup .
Michaelophorus indentatus is a species of moth in the genus Michaelophorus , known from Belize , Brazil , Mexico , and Panama .
The genus Cibolaites is a strongly ribbed and nodose ammonoid cephalopod from the middle Cretaceous of western New Mexico , included in the taxonomic family Collignoniceratidae .
Partula langfordi is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
The family , Sactorthoceratidae , was established by Rousseau Flower in 1946 , based on the genus Sactorthoceras .
Pseudapocryptes is a genus of gobies native to fresh and brackish waters of the Indian Ocean and Pacific Ocean coasts from India to Tahiti .
The Euliini are a tribe of tortrix moths .
Notonectidae is a cosmopolitan family of aquatic insects in the order Hemiptera , commonly called Backswimmers because they swim upside down .
Lithocarpus edulis ( common name , Japanese Stone Oak ) is a species of stone - oak native to Japan .
Tamarix nilotica , the Nile tamarisk , is a species of shrub or small tree in the tamarisk family .
Nebria cameroni is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Nepal and Uttar Pradesh province of India .
Astragalus missouriensis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Missouri milkvetch .
Charaxes nyikensis is a member of the large species group Charaxes etheocles
Ferrissia tanganyicensis is a species of small freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod in the family Planorbidae .
Hypselobarbus periyarensis is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Periyar Lake in Kerala , India .
Uromastyx geyri is a species of lizard belonging to the family Agamidae .
Sedum moraniii is a rare species of flowering plant in the stonecrop genus known by the common name Rogue River stonecrop .
Aphthona cyparissiae is a species of leaf beetle known as the brown dot leafy spurge flea beetle .
Sub species include Eucalyptus scias subsp .
Noctiluca scintillans , commonly known as the Sea Sparkle , and also published as Noctiluca miliaris , is a free - living non - parasitic marine - dwelling species of dinoflagellate that exhibits bioluminescence when disturbed ( popularly known as mareel ) .
Angraecum gabonense is a species of comet orchid that can be found in Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Equatorial Guinea and Gabon .
Shigella dysenteriae is a species of the rod - shaped bacterial genus Shigella .
Siboglinidae , also known as the beard worms , is a family of polychaete annelid worms whose members made up the former phyla Pogonophora ( the giant tube worms ) and Vestimentifera .
Cherublemma emmelas , the black brotula , is a species of cusk - eel found along the Pacific coast of Central and South America from Baja California to Chile .
Vellodius etisoides is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae .
Amazonspinther dalmata is a species of characin endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the Rio Purus and Rio Madeira basins .
Amara amplipennis is a species of beetle of the genus Amara in the Carabidae family that can be found in Asia .
Dendrobium sanguinolentum , the Blood - stained Dendrobium , is a species of flowering plant in the Orchidaceae family .
Eriochloa polystachya is a species of grass known by the common name Caribbean cupgrass .
Oplegnathus is currently the sole recognized genus in the knifejaw family ( Oplegnathidae ) of marine perciform fishes .
Reef lobsters , Enoplometopus , are a genus of small lobsters that live on reefs in the Indo - Pacific , Caribbean and warmer parts of the east Atlantic Ocean .
Aromobates capurinensis ( common name : Sierra Nevada rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Chlorothraupis is a genus of bird in the family Cardinalidae .
Sidalcea robusta is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name Butte County checkerbloom .
Stagmomantis montana ( Rehn , 1935 ) , common name Mountain mantis , is a species of praying mantis in genus Stagmomantis .
Billbergia viridiflora is a species in the genus Billbergia native to Tabasco , Belize and Guatemala .
Eupomatia is a genus of three flowering shrub species known to science , of the Australian continent ancient family Eupomatiaceae .
Geosesarma malayanum is a species of small red crab which is found in Malaysia .
Xyris , the yelloweyed grasses , is a genus of flowering plants in the Yellow - eyed - grass family .
Stirellus bicolor is a species of leafhopper native to North America .
Pentastelma is a genus of liana in family Apocynaceae , first published as a genus in 1974 .
Vernonia lettermannii , the narrowleaf ironweed , is a plant species known only from Arkansas and Oklahoma .
Dipteropeltis hirundo is a little - known species of fish louse .
Baobab is the common name for each of the nine species of tree in the genus Adansonia .
Theropithecus darti is an extinct species of Gelada from the middle to late Pliocene of Africa .
Manfreda longiflora is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae that is native to the Lower Rio Grande Valley of Texas in the United States and northern Tamaulipas in Mexico .
Tinguarra montana is a species of plants in the Apiaceae family , endemic to the Canary Islands .
Cacyparis elegans is a moth species in the genus Cacyparis found in the Solomon Islands .
Acrolophia is a genus of orchids , with 7 species , all endemic to South Africa .
Parthenopidae is a family of crabs , placed in its own superfamily , Parthenopoidea .
Pardosa profuga is a wolf spider species in the genus Pardosa found in Hungary .
Bidens torta , the corkscrew beggarticks , is a flowering plant species in the sunflower family .
Choreutidae , or metalmark moths , are a family of insects in the lepidopteran order whose relationships have been long disputed .
Bonnetia holostyla is a species of flowering plant in the Bonnetiaceae family .
Erosaria turdus , common name : the thrush cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
The genus Ecprepaulax was named by Hahn G. and Hahn R. in 1999 based on a single species Ecprepaulax anomala Fossil remains were found in Berriasian ( Lower Cretaceous ) strata in Portugal .
Quercus asymetrica is a species of oak in the subgenus Cyclobalanopsis .
Phacelia stebbinsii is an uncommon species of phacelia known by the common name Stebbins ' phacelia .
Cyperus bulbosus is a species of sedge found across Africa , the Middle East , Indian Subcontinent , Southeast Asia , and Australia .
Nanobamus is an extinct genus of amphibamid temnospondyl amphibian .
Saccharum is a genus of tall perennial plants of the broomsedge tribe within the grass family .
Catocala sponsa , the dark crimson underwing , is a species of moth of the Erebidae family .
Cattleya pumila , commonly known as the Dwarf Sophronitis , is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern and southern Brazil .
It is native to Brazil and is the only member of the genus Sellocharis .
Omobranchus robertsi is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific ocean , around Papua New Guinea .
Ascocratera is a genus of fungi within the Trypetheliaceae family .
Archontophoenix myolensis , the Myola Palm , is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
Platyphora testudo is a species of broad - shouldered leaf beetles belonging to the Chrysomelidae family .
Ziziphus abyssinica is a species of shrub in the Rhamnaceae family .
Psilostrophe , the paperflowers is a genus of North American plants in the sneezeweed tribe within the sunflower family .
It contains only the species Protomeroleuca perlides Berio , 1966 from Madagascar .
Kangnasaurus ( meaning `` Farm Kangnas lizard '' ) is a genus of iguanodontian ornithopod dinosaur found in supposedly Early Cretaceous rocks of South Africa .
Holoperas oenochroalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Holoperas .
Valentina Bartolomasi ( 1889 - 1932 ) was an Italian soprano who had a major opera career from 1910 through 1927 .
Antonietta Pastori ( born in 1929 ) is an Italian operatic soprano , particularly associated with lighter lyric and coloratura roles .
Darren Keith Woods ( born 1958 , Texas ) is an American opera director and operatic tenor .
Milena Kitic ( born 1968 in Belgrade , Yugoslavia ) is a Serbian American operatic mezzo - soprano .
Hector Dupeyron ( 1861 - -1911 ) was a French operatic tenor who had a prolific opera career in Europe from 1887 through 1906 .
David Habbin is a tenor from Ringwood , Hampshire , England , who achieved international acclaim as a founding member of the pop opera band , Amici Forever .
Michael Weinius , born March 1 , 1971 in Stockholm , is a Swedish tenor opera singer .
Lucien Muratore ( 29 August 1876 - 16 July 1954 , Paris ) was a French actor and operatic tenor , particularly associated with the French repertory .
Paul Schöffler ( 15 September 1897 -- 21 November 1977 ) was a German operatic baritone , particularly associated with Mozart , Wagner , and Strauss roles .
Nicholas Isherwood is US - born bass singer , who specialises in contemporary and baroque music .
Lei Jia ( Chinese : 雷佳 ; pinyin : Léi Jīa , born October 19 , 1979 in Yiyang , Hunan ) is a Chinese folk soprano and a Chinese national class one performer .
Karl Perron , born Karl Pergamenter and also known as Carl Perron , ( 3 June 1858 -- 15 July 1928 ) was a German bass - baritone .
Russell Braun ( born 19 July 1965 ) is a Canadian operatic lyric baritone , Juno Award winner .
Amanda Forsythe ( born 1976 ) is an award winning American light lyric soprano who is particularly admired for her interpretations of baroque music and the works of Rossini .
Marinka Gurewich ( 1902 , Bratislava - 23 December 1990 , Manhattan ) was an American voice teacher and mezzo - soprano of Jewish Czech descent .
Graeme Danby ( born 23 May 1962 in Consett , County Durham , England ) is an operatic bass who has performed at several of the world 's leading opera houses , notably the Royal Opera House , Covent Garden and the English National Opera .
Janet Price ( born 1941 ) is a Welsh soprano particularly associated with the 19th - century Italian bel canto repertory .
Euphrosyne Parepa - Rosa ( 7 May 1836 -- 21 January 1874 ) was a British operatic soprano who established the Carl Rosa Opera Company together with second husband Carl Rosa .
Bonaventura Bottone ( born 19 September 1950 in London ) is an operatic tenor who has performed at many of the world 's leading opera houses .
Hugo Hasslo ( 16 May 1911 Bohuslän - 20 January 1994 Stockholm ) was a Swedish operatic baritone .
Theodore Harrison was a Chicago - area concert baritone and choral conductor best known for his presence in the Chicago music community .
Ashley Putnam ( born August 10 , 1952 ) is an American soprano from New York City .
Ilse Gramatzki ( born 1939 ) is a German operatic mezzo - soprano and contralto who performed at major European opera houses .
Günter Reich ( 22 November 1921 -- 15 January 1989 ) , also spelled Günther Reich and Gunther Reich , was an Israeli baritone of German birth .
Ryan Allen is an American bass singer best known for his work in opera .
Miriam Pirazzini ( born August 21 , 1918 ) was a well - known Italian mezzo - soprano .
Franz Betz ( 19 March 1835 -- 11 August 1900 ) was a German bass - baritone opera singer who sang at the Berlin State Opera from 1859 to 1897 .
Anita Cerquetti ( 13 April 1931 -- 11 October 2014 ) was an Italian dramatic soprano who had a short but meteoric career in the 1950s .
Valeria Stenkina ( Russian : Валерия Стенкина ) is a Russian operatic soprano and Meritorious Artist of Russia .
Ecuador 's foremost classical soprano , Beatriz Parra Durango was born in Guayaquil in 1940 .
Cesare Valletti ( December 18 , 1922 - May 13 , 2000 ) was an Italian operatic tenor , one of the leading tenore di grazia of the postwar era .
Susan Owen ( married : Susan Owen - Leinert ) is an American operatic soprano .
Joshua Hecht is an operatic bass .
